obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (45477)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45477&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Indian Stamp`
  line `Act, 1899.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2***:`
  line
  line `Provided that it shall not apply to ^3[the territories which, immediately before the 1st November, 1956,`
  line `were comprised in Part B States] (excluding the State of Jammu and Kashmir) except to the extent to`
  line `which the provisions of this Act relate to rates of stamp-duty in respect of the documents specified in`
  line `Entry 91 of List I in the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution].`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on the first day of July, 1899.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 1955, s. 3, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-4-1956).`
  line
  line `2. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10- 2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. (No. 2) 1956, for "Part B States".`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (45478)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45478&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is something repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `^1[(1) Allotment list.--"allotment list" means a list containing details of allotment of the securities`
  line `intimated by the issuer to the depository under sub-section (2) of section 8 of the Depositories Act,`
  line `1996 (22 of 1996);`
  line
  line `(1A) "banker" includes a bank and any person acting as a banker;]`
  line
  line `(2) Bill of exchange-- "bill of exchange" means a bill of exchange as defined by the Negotiable Instruments Act, 1881, (26 of 1881), and includes also a hundi, and any other document entitling or purporting to entitle any person, whether named therein or not, to payment by any other person of, or to draw upon any other person for, any sum of money;`
  line
  line `(3) Bill of exchange payable on demand-- "bill of exchange payable on demand" includes`
  line
  line `(a) an order for the payment of any sum of money by a bill of exchange or promissory note, or for the delivery of any bill of exchange or promissory note in satisfaction of any sum of money, or for the payment of any sum of money out of any particular fund which may or may not be available, or upon any condition or contingency which may or may not be performed or happen;`
  line
  line `(b) an order for the payment of any sum of money weekly, monthly, or at any other stated period; and`
  line
  line `(c) a letter of credit, that is to say, any instrument by which one person authorizes another to give credit to the person in whose favour it is drawn:`
  line
  line `(4) Bill of lading. "bill of lading" includes a through bill lading, but does not include a mate's receipt:`
  line
  line `(5) Bond-- "bond" includes--`
  line
  line `(a) any instrument whereby a person obliges himself to pay money to another, on condition that the obligation shall be void if a specified act is performed, or is not performed, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) any instrument attested by a witness and not payable to order or bearer, whereby a person obliges himself to pay money to another; and`
  line
  line `(c) any instrument so attested, whereby a person obliges himself to deliver grain or other agricultural produce to another;`
  line
  line `^2[but does not include a debenture;]`
  line
  line `(6) Chargeable-- "chargeable" means, as applied to an instrument executed or first executed after the commencement of this Act, chargeable under this Act, and, as applied to any other instrument, chargeable under the law in force in ^3[India] when such instrument was executed or, where several persons executed the instrument at different times, first executed;`
  line
  line `(7) Cheque-- "cheque" means a bill of exchange drawn on a specified banker and not expressed to be payable otherwise than on demand;`
  line
  line `^4[(7A) "clearance list " means a list of transactions of sale and purchase relating to contracts traded`
  line `on the stock exchanges submitted to a clearing corporation in accordance with the law for the time`
  line `being in force in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(7B) "clearing corporation " means an entity established to undertake the activity of clearing and`
  line `settlement of transactions in securities or other instruments and includes a clearing house of a`
  line `recognised stock exchange;]`
  line
  line ^5*****
  line
  line `(9) Collector. "Collector"--`
  line
  line `(a) means, within the limits of the towns of Calcutta, Madras and Bombay, the Collector of Calcutta, Madras and Bombay, respectively, and, without those limits, the Collector of a district, and`
  line
  line `(b) includes a Deputy Commissioner and any officer whom ^6the ^7State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(10) Conveyance-- conveyance includes a conveyance on sale every instrument by which property, whether moveable or immovable, is transferred inter vivos and which is not otherwise specifically provided for by schedule I;`
  line
  line `^8[(10A) debenturte.--"debenture" includes--`
  line
  line `(i) debenture stock, bonds or any other instrument of a company evidencing a debt, whether`
  line `constituting a charge on the assets of the company or not;`
  line
  line `(ii) bonds in the nature of debenture issued by any incorporated company or body corporate;`
  line
  line `(iii) certificate of deposit, commercial usance bill, commercial paper and such other debt`
  line `instrument of original or initial maturity upto one year as the Reserve Bank of India may specify`
  line `from time to time;`
  line
  line `(iv) securitised debt instruments; and`
  line
  line `(v) any other debt instruments specified by the Securities and Exchange Board of India from`
  line `time to time;`
  line
  line `(10B) "depository" includes--`
  line
  line `(a) a depository as defined in clause (e) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Depositories`
  line `Act, 1996 (22 of 1996); and`
  line
  line `(b) any other entity declared by the Central Government, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, to be a depository for the purposes of this Act;]`
  line
  line `(11) Duly stamped-- "duly stamped", as applied to an instrument, means that the instrument`
  line `bears an adhesive or impressed stamp of not less than the proper amount and that such stamp has been`
  line `affixed or used in accordance with the law for the time being in force in ^9[India]:`
  line
  line `(12) Executed and execution-- executed and execution used with reference to instruments, mean signed and signature;`
  line
  line ^10******
  line
  line `(13) Impressed stamp-- "impressed stamp" includes--`
  line
  line `(a) labels affixed and impressed by the proper officer; and`
  line
  line `(b) stamps embossed or engraved on stamped paper;`
  line
  line `^11[(13A) India-- "India" means the territory of India excluding the State of Jammu and Kashmir;]`
  line
  line `^12[(14) "instrument" includes--`
  line
  line `(a) every document, by which any right or liability is, or purports to be, created, transferred,`
  line `limited, extended, extinguished or recorded;`
  line
  line `(b) a document, electronic or otherwise, created for a transaction in a stock exchange or`
  line `depository by which any right or liability is, or purports to be, created, transferred, limited,`
  line `extended, extinguished or recorded; and`
  line
  line `(c) any other document mentioned in Schedule I,`
  line
  line `but does not include such instruments as may be specified by the Government, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette.]`
  line
  line `(15) Instrument of partition-- "instrument of partition" means any instrument where by coowners of any property divide or agree to divide such property in severalty, and includes also a final order for effecting a partition passed by any Revenue-authority or any Civil Court and an award by an arbitrator directing a partition;`
  line
  line `^13[(15A) Issue. --"issue" means any person making an issue of securities;]`
  line
  line `(16) Lease-- "lease" means a lease of immovable property, and includes also`
  line
  line `(a) a patta;`
  line
  line `(b) a kabuliyat or other undertaking in writing, not being a counterpart of a lease, to cultivate, occupy, or pay or deliver rent for, immovable property;`
  line
  line `(c) any instrument by which tolls of any description are let;`
  line
  line `(d) any writing on an application for a lease intended to signify that the application is granted;`
  line
  line `^14[(16A) Marketable security.-- "marketable security" means a security capable of being traded in`
  line `any stock exchange in India;`
  line
  line `(16B) Market value.--"market value", in relation to an instrument through which--`
  line
  line `(a) any security is traded in a stock exchange, means the price at which it is so traded;`
  line
  line `(b) any security which is transferred through a depository but not traded in the stock exchange,`
  line `means the price or the consideration mentioned in such instrument;`
  line
  line `(c) any security is dealt otherwise than in the stock exchange or depository, means the price or`
  line `consideration mentioned in such instrument;]`
  line
  line `(17) Mortgage-deed-- "mortgage-deed" includes every instrument whereby, for the purpose of securing money advanced, or to be advanced, by way of loan, or an existing or future debt, or the performance of an engagement, one person transfers, or creates, to, or in favour of, another, a right over or in respect of specified property;`
  line
  line `(18) Paper-- "paper" includes vellum, parchment or any other material on which an instrument may be written;`
  line
  line `(19) Policy of insurance-- "policy of insurance includes"--`
  line
  line `(a) any instrument by which one person, in consideration of a premium, engages to indemnify another against loss, damage or liability arising from an unknown or contingent event;`
  line
  line `(b) a life-policy, and any policy insuring any person against accident or sickness, and any other personal insurance; ^15***`
  line
  line `^16* * * * *`
  line
  line `^17[(19A) "Policy of group insurance"-- "policy of group insurance" means any instrument covering not less than fifty or such smaller number as the Central Government may approve, either generally or with reference to any particular case, by which an insurer, in consideration of a premium paid by an employer or by an employer and his employees jointly, engages to cover, with or without medical examination and for the sole benefit of persons other than the employer, the lives of all the employees or of any class of them, determined by conditions pertaining to the employment, for amounts of insurance based upon a plan which precludes individual selection :]`
  line
  line `(20) Policy of sea-insurance or sea-policy-- "Policy of sea-insurance" or "sea-policy"--`
  line
  line `(a) means any insurance made upon any ship or vessel (whether for marine or inland navigation), or upon the machinery, tackle or furniture of any ship or vessel, or upon any goods, merchandise or property of any description whatever on board of any ship or vessel, or upon the freight of, or any other interest which may be lawfully insured in, or relating to, any ship or vessel; and`
  line
  line `(b) includes any insurance of goods, merchandise or property for any transit which includes, not only a sea risk within the meaning of clause (a), but also any other risk incidental to the transit insured from the commencement of the transit to the ultimate destination covered by the insurance;`
  line
  line `Where any person, in consideration of any sum of money paid or to be paid for additional freight or otherwise, agrees to take upon himself any risk attending goods, merchandise or property of any description whatever while on board of any ship or vessel, or engages to indemnify the owner of any such goods, merchandise or property from any risk, loss or damage, such agreement or engagement shall be deemed to be a contract for sea-insurance;`
  line
  line `(21) Power-of-attorney-- "power-of-attorney" includes any instrument (not chargeable with a fee under the law relating to Court-fees for the time being in force) empowering a specified person to act for and in the name of the person executing it:`
  line
  line `(22) Promissory note-- "promissory note" means a promissory note as defined by the Negotiable Instruments Act, 1881 (XXVI of 1881);`
  line
  line `It also includes a note promising the payment of any sum of money out of any particular fund which may or may not be available, or upon any condition or contingency which may or may not be performed or happen;`
  line
  line `(23) Receipt-- "receipt" includes any note, memorandum or writing`
  line
  line `(a) whereby any money or any bill of exchange, cheque or promissory note is acknowledged to have been received, or--`
  line
  line `(b) whereby any other moveable property is acknowledged to have been received in satisfaction of a debt, or`
  line
  line `(c) where by any debt or demand, or any part of a debt or demand, is acknowledged to have been satisfied or discharged, or`
  line
  line `(d) which signifies or imports any such acknowledgment,`
  line
  line `and whether the same is or is not signed with the name of any person; ^18***`
  line
  line `^19[(23A) Securities.--dbqtdsecurities" includes--`
  line
  line `(i) securities as defined in clause (h) of section 2 of the Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act,`
  line `1956 (42 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(ii) a "derivative" as defined in clause (a) of section 45U of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934`
  line `(2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(iii) a certificate of deposit, commercial usance bill, commercial paper, repo on corporate bonds`
  line `and such other debt instrument of original or initial maturity upto one year as the Reserve Bank of`
  line `India ma specify from time to time; and`
  line
  line `(iv) any other instrument declared by the Central Government, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, to be securities for the purposes of this Act.]`
  line
  line `(24) Settlement--"settlement" means any non-testamentary disposition, in writing, of moveable or immovable property made--`
  line
  line `(a) in consideration of marriage,`
  line
  line `(b) for the purpose of distributing property of the settler among his family or those for whom he desires to provide, or for the purpose of providing for some person dependent on him, or`
  line
  line `(c) for any religious or charitable purpose;`
  line
  line `and includes an agreement in writing to make such a disposition ^20and, where any such disposition has not been made in writing, any instrument recording, whether by way of declaration of trust or otherwise, the terms of any such disposition; ^21***`
  line
  line `^22[(25) Soldier-- "soldier" includes any person below the rank of non-commissioned officer who is enrolled under the ^23Indian Army Act, 1911 (8 of 1911).]`
  line
  line `^24[(26) Stamp. "stamp" means any mark, seal or endorsement by any agency or person duly authorised by the State Government, and includes an adhesive or impressed stamp, for the purposes of duty chargeable under this Act.]`
  line
  line `^25[(27) Stock exchange.-- "stock exchange" includes--`
  line
  line `(i) a recognised stock exchange as defined in clause (f) of section 2 of the Securities Contracts`
  line `(Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956); and`
  line
  line `(ii) such other platform for trading or reporting a deal in securities, as may be specified by the`
  line `Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, for the purposes of this Act.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Assam--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2 of Act II of 1892.--In section 2 of the principal Act, after clause (7), the`
  line `following shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(8) "Chief Controlling Revenue Authority" means the Superintendent of Stamps, Assam."`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 10 of 1968, s. 2]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Himachal Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2.-- In clause (10) of section 2 of the Indian Stamp Act, 1899, hereinafter referred to as the said Act, for the colon shall be substituted a comma, followed by the words "or by Schedule I-A as the case may be.`
  line
  line `[Vide Himachal Pradesh Act 4 of 1953, s. 2]`
  line
  line Uttarakhand.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2.--Indian Stamp (Uttarakhand Amendment) Bill, 2011 (as passed by the`
  line `Uttarakhand Legislative Assembly on dated 16 March, 2011) clause 9 shall be substituted as follows;`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `"Voting or attempting to cote under any proxy not duly stamped shall for every such offence, be`
  line `punishable with fine which may extend to five thousand."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 20 of 2013, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2.--In section 2 of the Indian Stamp Act, 1899 (hereinafter referred to as the`
  line `principal Act),:--`
  line
  line `(a) For clause (14), the following clause shall be substituted; namely:--`
  line
  line `(14) "Instrument" instrument includes every document and record created or maintained in or`
  line `by an electronic storage and retrieval device or media by which any right or liability is, or purports`
  line `to be, created, transferred, limited, extended, extinguished or recorded;`
  line
  line `(b) After clause (14), the following clause shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `(14-A) "Instrument of Gift" Instrument of gift includes an instrument whether by way of`
  line `declaration or otherwise, for making or accepting an oral gift;`
  line
  line `(c) After clause (22), the following clause shall be inserted namely:--`
  line
  line `(22-A) "Public Officer" Public Officer means a Public Officer as defined in clause (17) of`
  line `section 2 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 and includes every officer working in connection`
  line `with the affairs of any of the following of the organizations, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) Any statutory body or authority Constituted under any Uttarakhand State Act;`
  line
  line `(b) A "Financing Bank" or "Central Bank" as defined in clause (L) of section 2 of the`
  line `Uttarakhand Cooperative Societies Act, 2003.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 1 of 2016, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 2 of Act no. 2 of 1899.In section 2 of the Indian Stamp Act, 1899,`
  line `hereinafter referred to as the principal Act, in clause (16), after sub-clause (d), the following clause shall`
  line `be inserted, namely :`
  line
  line `(e) any instrument by which mining lease is granted in respect of minor minerals as defined in`
  line `clause (e) of section 3 of the Mines and Minerals (Regulation and Development) Act, 1957.`
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 11 of 1992, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2 of Act II of 1899.In section 2 of the Indian Stamp Act, 1899 as amended`
  line `in its application to Uttar Pradesh, hereinafter in this Chapter referred to as the principal Act, in clause (10), the following Explanation shall be inserted in the end, namely :`
  line
  line `Explanation An instrument whereby a co-owner of a property having defined share therein,`
  line `transfers such share or part thereof to another co-owner of the property, is for the purposes of this clause`
  line `an instrument by which property is transferred.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 19 of 1981, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2 of Act II of 1899.-- In section 2 of the Indian Stamp Act, 1899, hereinafter`
  line `referred to as the principal Act, for clause (15), the following clause shall be substituted, namely :--`
  line
  line `"(15) "instrument of partition" means any instrument whereby co-owners of any property divide`
  line `or agree to divide such property in severalty, and also includes---`
  line
  line `(i) a final order for effecting a partition passed by any revenue authority or any civil court ;`
  line
  line `(ii) an award by an arbitrator directing a partition ; and`
  line
  line `(iii) when any partition is effected without executing any such instrument, any instrument of`
  line `instruments signed by the co-owners and recording, whether by way of declaration of such`
  line `partition or otherwise, the terms of such partition amongst the co-owners ;--`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 20 of 1974, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2 of Act no. 2 of 1899.---In section 2 of the Indian Stamp Act, 1899,`
  line `hereinafter referred to as the Amendment of principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) for sub-section (14), the following sub-section shall be substituted, namely-`
  line `"(14) Instrument" "Instrument includes every document and record created or maintained in`
  line `or by an electronic storage and retrieval device or media by which any right or liability is, or`
  line `purports to be, created, transferred, limited, extended, extinguished or recorded;`
  line
  line `(b) after sub-section (14), the following sub-section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `(14-A) 'Instrument of Gift' '1nstrument of Gift' includes an instrument whether by way of`
  line `declaration or otherwise, for making or accepting an oral gift;`
  line
  line `(c) after sub-section (22), the following sub-section shall be inserted, namely :--`
  line
  line `(22-A) 'Public Officer' Public Officer' means a Public Officer as defined in clause (17) of`
  line `section 2 of the Code of Civil procedure, 1908 and includes every officer working in connection`
  line `with the affairs of any of the following of organizations, namely :---`
  line
  line `(a) any statutory body or authority constituted under any Uttar Pradesh Act;`
  line
  line `(b) a 'Financing Bank or 'Central Bank' as defined in clause (k) of section 2 of the Uttar`
  line `Pradesh Co-operative Societies Act, 1965 ;`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 38 of 2001, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2 of Act II of 1899.-- In section 2 of the Indian Stamp Act, 1899, as`
  line `amended in its application to Uttar Pradesh (hereinafter referred to as the principal Act), after clause (26-`
  line `A), the following clause shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `27. 'quarter' means a quarter of the financial year.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 49 of 1975, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 12, for clause (1) (w.e.f. 1-7-2020).[Earlier notified w.e.f. 9-1-2020 followed by 1-4-2020]`
  line
  line `2. Added by Act 7 of 2019, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-7-2020). [Earlier notified w.e.f. 9-1-2020 followed by 1-4-2020]`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 43 of 1955, s. 2, for "the States" (w.e.f. 1-4-1956).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-7-2020). [Earlier notified w.e.f. 9-1-2020 followed by 1-4-2020]`
  line
  line `5. Clause (8) omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "the L.G.".`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "collecting Government".`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-7-2020). [Earlier notified w.e.f. 9-1-2020 followed by 1-4-2020]`
  line
