obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (45568)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Instruments chargeable with duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45568&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act and the exemptions`
  line `contained in Schedule I, the following instruments shall be chargeable with duty of the amount indicated in that Schedule as the proper duty therefore respectively, that is to say--`
  line
  line `(a) every instrument mentioned in that Schedule which, not having been previously executed by any person, is executed in ^1[India] on or after the first day of July, 1899;`
  line
  line `(b) every bill of exchange ^2[payable otherwise than on demand] ^3*** or promissory note drawn or made out of ^1[India ]on or after that day and accepted or paid, or presented for acceptance or payment, or endorsed, transferred or otherwise negotiated, in ^1[India]; and`
  line
  line `(c) every instrument (other than a bill of exchange, ^3***or promissory note) mentioned in that Schedule, which, not having been previously executed by any person, is executed out of ^1[India] on or after that day, relates to any property situate, or to any matter or thing done or to be done, in ^1[India] and is received in ^1India:`
  line
  line `Provided that no duty shall be chargeable in respect of--`
  line
  line `(1) any instrument executed by, or on behalf of, or in favour of, the Government in cases where, but for this exemption, the Government would be liable to pay the duty chargeable in respect of such instrument;`
  line
  line `(2) any instrument for the sale, transfer or other disposition, either absolutely or by way of mortgage or otherwise, of any ship or vessel, or any part, interest, share or property of or in any ship or vessel registered under the Merchant Shipping Act 1894, Act No. 57 & 58 Vict. c. 60 or under Act XIX of 1838 Act No. or the Indian Registration of Ships Act, 1841, (CX of 1841) as amended by subsequent Acts.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Himachal Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 3.-- In section 3 of the said Act- (1) After clause (c), the following proviso shall be inserted, namely: --- "Provided that, notwithstanding anything contained in clauses (a), (b) or (c) of this section or in Schedule I, and subject to the exemptions contained in Schedule I-A, the following instruments shall be chargeable with duty of the amount indicated in Schedule I-A, as the proper duty therefor, respectively, that is to say:`
  line
  line `(aa) every instrument mentioned in Schedule I-A as chargeable with duty under that Schedule which, not having been previously executed by any person is executed in the Himachal Pradesh on or after the date of commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(bb) every instrument mentioned in Schedule I-A as chargeable with duty under that Schedule, which, not having been previously executed by any person, is executed out of Himachal Pradesh, on or after the date of commencement of this Act and relates to any property situated, or to any matter or thing done or to be done in the Himachal Pradesh, and is received in the Himachal Pradesh".`
  line
  line `(2) Between the word Provided and the words that no duty the word also shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Himachal Pradesh Act 4 of 1953, s. 3]`
  line
  line Odisha.--
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 3A.--After section 3 of the Indian Stamp Act, 1899, (2 of 1899) the`
  line `following section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"3.A Duty chargeable on mining lease. -- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act and`
  line `the rules made thereunder, on every instrument of grant or renewal of a mining lease, the stamp duty`
  line `chargeable shall be equivalent to fifteen percentum of the amount of average royalty that would accrue`
  line `out of the highest annual extraction of minerals permitted under the approved mining plan or mining`
  line `scheme, as the case may be, for such mining lease under the relevant law in force, multiplied by the`
  line `period of such mining lease.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this sub-section, the average royalty of the highest grade of minerals`
  line `based on the date available for past twelve months beginning from the date of commencement of the`
  line `Indian Stamp (Odisha Amendment) Act, 2013 shall be taken into consideration:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an application for renewal of mining lease has been made to the State`
  line `Government prior to the expiry of the lease, but renewal of lease has not been granted by the State`
  line `Government or the mining lease is deemed to have been extended by a further period in accordance with`
  line `the provisions contained in the relevant law in force, till the State Government passes an order, prior to`
  line `the commencement of the Indian Stamp (Odisha Amendment) Act, 2013, the sum total of the quantity of`
  line `mineral permitted for extraction, year wise, in the approved mining plan or mining scheme, as the`
  line `case, may be, or the actual quantity raised, whichever is higher, shall be taken into consideration for`
  line `calculation of the stamp duty:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in case the production level is enhanced on account of subsequent modification`
  line `or review of the mining plan, the stamp lease period and the lessee shall deposit the differential stamp`
  line `duty before such enhancement is carried out by him:`
  line
  line `Provided also that in case a lessee is required to surrender the mining lease or, permanently prohibited`
  line `from undertaking the extraction of mineral by, or for reasons of any operation of law, court orders passed`
  line `or any order issued under any law for the time being in force and the reasons of such prohibition are not`
  line `in any manner attributable to such lessee or his agents, servants, employees or persons claiming through`
  line `or under such lessee, the lessee shall be entitled for refund of the stamp duty paid by him to the extent of`
  line `such balance period of lease outstanding:`
  line
  line `Provided also that where the lessee is prohibited from undertaking the extraction of minerals for a`
  line `temporary period for the reasons mentioned in the third proviso and subject to the conditions specified`
  line `therein, the stamp duty chargeable shall be equivalent to the amount of the sum total of the dead rent that`
  line `would be payable for the mining lease under the relevant law in force, for the period of such prohibition.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an application for renewal of a mining lease has been made to the State Government prior`
  line `to the expiry of the lease but renewal of the lease has not been granted by the State Government or the`
  line `mining lease is deemed to have been extended as per the provisions contained in the relevant law in force,`
  line `by a further period till the State Government passes an order thereon, the stamp duty payable under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be paid by the applicant on or before the date of expiry of the lease or within sixty`
  line `days from the date of commencement of the Indian Stamp (Odisha Amendment) Act, 2013, whichever is`
  line `later, the manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) If the application for grant or renewal of mining lease is rejected by the State Government, the`
  line `applicant shall be entitled for refund of full stamp duty by him without any interest.`
  line
  line `(4) In case of a mining lease whose period is deemed to have been extended by a further period till the`
  line `State Government passes an order thereon and the State Government, at a later date, passes an order`
  line `rejecting the renewal of the lease, the applicant shall be entitled for refund of such amount of stamp duty`
  line `paid under sub-section (1), as arrived at by deducting from the total amount of stamp duty paid, the`
  line `amount of stamp duty chargeable in respect of such mining lease till the date of such rejection order`
  line `without any interest.`
  line
  line `(5) No refund as mentioned in sub-sections (3) and (4) shall be made if the order rejecting the`
  line `application is challenged or the time limit for presenting the application for revision of the order of`
  line `rejection is not expired".`
  line
  line `[Vide Odisha Act 16 of 2013, s. 2]`
  line
  line Meghalaya.--
  line
  line `Insertion of a new section in Central Act II of 1899.--After section 3 of the Indian Stamp Act,`
  line `1899, the following shall be inserted as section 3A, namely:--`
  line
  line `"3A. Surcharge on Stamp Duty.--(1) There shall be charged, levied and paid to the`
  line `Government of Meghalaya, besides payable under any law for the time being in force including`
  line `section 3 of this Act, a surcharge, herein after referred to as Stamp Surcharge on the instruments`
  line `mention on the following items of Schedule I of the principal Act, namely:--`
  line
  line `Item Nos. 1-10, 12,15-20, 22-26, 28, 29,31,38-46,48,50, 51, 54-61 and 63-65.`
  line
  line `Provided that the surcharge shall not be payable in respect of instruments exempted by section 3.`
  line
  line `(2) The rate of Stamp Surcharge shall be twenty, Five paisa per instrument.`
  line
  line `(3) The Stamp Surcharge shall be payable as if it were a duty under section 3 and the provisions`
  line `of this Act including the rules thereunder shall according apply; and the authorities for the time`
  line `being empowered to collect and enforce payment of stamp duty shall, unless otherwise provided for`
  line `by or under the Act, within their respective jurisdiction for purpose of stamp duty accordingly`
  line `collect and enforce payment of stamp Surcharge.`
  line
  line `Provide that the Government of Meghalaya may, for facilitating implementation, by`
  line `notification, direct that in any case or class the provisions of this act including the rules thereunder`
  line `shall apply subject to such indications not inconsistent with the provisions of this section and as`
  line `may be specified in such notification.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3), the Government of Meghalaya may`
  line `make rule generally for securing the payment of the Stamp Surcharge and carrying into effect the`
  line `provisions the sub-sections (1) and (2) and in particular for ensuring the proper maintenance and`
  line `rendering or accounts of the Stamp Surcharge."`
  line
  line `[Vide Meghalaya Act 13 of 1972, s. 2]`
  line
  line Meghalaya.--
  line
  line `Insertion of a new section in Central Act II of 1899.--After section 3 of the Indian Stamp Act, 1899`
  line `the following shall be inserted as section 3A, namely:--`
  line
  line `"3A. Surcharge on Stamp Duty.--(1) There shall be charged, levied and paid to the Government of`
  line `Meghalaya, besides payable under any law for the time being in force including section 3 of this Act,`
  line `a surcharge, hereinafter referred to as Stamp Surcharge on the instruments mentioned in the following`
  line `items of Schedule I to the principal Act, namely:--`
  line
  line `Item Nos. 1-10, 12, 15-20, 22-26, 28, 29, 31, 36, 38-46, 48, 50, 51, 54-61 and 63-65.`
  line
  line `Provided that the surcharge shall not be payable in respect of instruments exempted by section 3.`
  line
  line `(2) The rate of Stamp Surcharge shall be twenty. Five paise per instrument.`
  line
  line `(3) The Stamp Surcharge shall by payable as if it were a duty under section 3 and the provisions`
  line `of this Act including the rules thereunder shall according apply; and the authorities for the time being`
  line `empowered to collect and enforce payment of stamp duty shall, unless otherwise provided for by or`
  line `under the Act, within their respective jurisdiction for purpose of stamp duty accordingly collect and`
  line `enforce payment of Stamp Surcharge.`
  line
  line `Provided that the Government of Meghalaya may, for facilitating implementation, by notification,`
  line `direct that in any case or class the provisions of this Act including the rules thereunder shall apply`
  line `subject to such indications not inconsistent with the provisions of this section and as may be specified`
  line `in such notification.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3), the Government of Meghalaya may`
  line `make rules generally for securing the payment of the Stamp Surcharge and carrying into effect the`
  line `provisions the sub-sections (1) and (2) and in particular for ensuring the proper maintenance and`
  line `rendering or accounts of the Stamp Surcharge."`
  line
  line `[Vide Meghalaya Act 15 of 1973, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 43 of 1955, s. 2, for the States (w.e.f. 1-4-1956).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 5 of 1927, s. 5.`
  line
  line `3. The word cheque omitted by s. 5, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_a:
  sectionId (45480)
  sectionNo 3A
  orderNo 4
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45480&sectionno=3A&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content:
  string
  line `[Instruments chargeable with additional duty.] Omitted by the Refugee Relief Taxes (Abolition) Act, 1973 (13 of 1973), s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line
  line Tripura.--
  line
  line `Substitution of section 3B.-- For section 3B of the principal Act, as inserted by the Union`
  line `Territories Taxation Laws (Amendment) Act, 1971, the following shall be substituted, namely: --`
  line
  line `"3B. Instrument Chargeable with additional duty.--(1) Every instrument chargeable with duty`
  line `under section 3, read with Schedule 1, not being an instrument mentioned articles Nos. 13, 14, 27, 37, 47,`
  line `49, 52, 53 or 62(a), shall, in addition to such duty, be chargeable with a duty of ten paise.`
  line `(2) The additional duty with which any instrument is chargeable under sub-section (1) shall be paid`
  line `and such payment shall be indicated on such instrument by means of adhesive stamp.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Tripura Act 5 of 1973, s. ]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (45481)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Several instruments used in single transaction of sale, mortgage or settlement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45481&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, in`
  line `the case of any sale, mortgage or settlement, several instruments are employed for completing the`
  line `transaction, the principal instrument only shall be chargeable with the duty prescribed in Schedule I, for`
  line `the conveyance, mortgage or settlement, and each of the other instruments shall be chargeable with a duty`
  line `of one rupee instead of the duty (if any) prescribed for it in that Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) The parties may determine for themselves which of the instrument so employed shall, for the`
  line `purposes of sub-section (1), be deemed to be the principal instrument:`
  line
  line `Provided that the duty chargeable on the instrument so determined shall be the highest duty which`
  line `would be chargeable in respect of any of the said instruments employed.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), in the case of any issue, sale or`
  line `transfer of securities, the instrument on which stamp-duty is chargeable under section 9A shall be the`
  line `principal instrument for the purpose of this section and no stamp-duty shall be charged on any other`
  line `instruments relating to any such transaction.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Himachal Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 4.-- In sub-section (1) of section 4 of the said Act--`
  line
  line `(a) for the word and figure "Schedule I" the word, figure and letter "Schedule I-A" shall be substituted, and`
  line
  line `(b) for the words one rupee, the words "two rupees" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Himachal Pradesh Act 4 of 1953, s. 4]`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 4. --In section 4 of the Indian Act, 1899 (2 of 1899) (hereinafter referred to as`
  line `the principal Act) in sub-section (1), for the words, "one rupee", and eight annas`
  line `the words`
  line `"ten rupees"`
  line `shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 1 of 2003, s. 2]`
  line
  line Manipur
  line
  line `Amendment of sections 4 and 6.-In sub-section (1) of section 4 and in the proviso to section 6 of the`
  line `Indian Stamp Act, 1899 s application to the State of Manipur hereinafter referred to as the Principal Act`
  line `the words "two rupees" wherever they occur, the words "two rupees and paise fifty" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Manipur Act 4 of 1989, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (45482)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Instruments relating to several distinct matters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45482&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Any instrument comprising or relating to`
  line `several distinct matters shall be chargeable with the aggregate amount of the duties with which separate`
  line `instruments, each comprising or relating to one of such matters, would be chargeable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (45483)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Instruments coming within several descriptions in Schedule I.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45483&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of the`
  line `last preceding section, an instrument so framed as to come within two or more of the descriptions in`
  line `Schedule I, shall, where the duties chargeable thereunder are different, be chargeable only with the`
  line `highest of such duties:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this Act contained shall render chargeable with duty exceeding one rupee a`
  line `counterpart or duplicate of any instrument chargeable with duty and in respect of which the proper duty`
  line `has been paid.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Himachal Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 6-- In section 6 of the said Act- (1) After the word and figure "Schedule I"`
  line `the words, figure and letter "or Schedule I-A" shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `(2) In the proviso, for the words "one rupee" the words "two rupees" shall be substituted and after the`
  line `words "has been paid" the following shall be added, namely;--`
  line
  line `"unless it falls within the provisions of section 6-A".`
  line
  line `[Vide Himachal Pradesh Act 4 of 1953, s. 5]`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 6.--In the proviso the section 6 of the principal Act, for the words "one rupees`
  line `and eight annas", the words "ten rupees" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 1 of 2003, s. 3]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Himachal Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Addition of a new section 6-A.--After section 6 of the said Act, the following new section shall be`
  line `inserted: --`
  line
  line `6-A. Payment of Himachal Pradesh stamp duty on copies, counter-parts or duplicates when that`
  line `duty has not been paid on the principal or original instrument.-- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in sections 4 or 6 or in any other law, unless it is proved that the duty chargeable under the Indian Stamp`
  line `(Himachal Pradesh Amendment) Act, 1952 has been paid:--`
  line
  line `(a) on the principal or original instrument as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `(b) in accordance with the provisions of this section, the duty chargeable on an instrument of sale,`
  line `mortgage or settlement other than a principal instrument or on a counterpart, duplicate or copy of any`
  line `instrument shall, if the principal or original instrument would, when received in Himachal Pradesh, have`
  line `been chargeable, under the Indian Stamp (Himachal Pradesh Amendment) Act, 1952, with a higher rate`
  line `of duty with which the principal or original instrument would have been chargeable under section 19-A.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 35 or in any other law, no instrument, counterpart,`
  line `duplicate or copy chargeable with duty under this section shall be received in evidence as properly`
  line `stamped unless the duty chargeable under this section has been paid thereon:`
  line
  line `Provided that a court before which any such instrument, counterpart, duplicate or copy is produced,`
  line `shall permit the duty chargeable under this section, to be paid thereon and shall then receive it in`
  line evidence.
  line
  line `[Vide Himachal Pradesh Act 4 of 1953, s. 6]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (45484)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Policies of sea-insurance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Sub-sections (1), (2) and (3) rep. by Act 11 of 1963, s. 92 (w.e.f. 1-8-1963).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45484&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `* * * **`
  line
  line `(4) Where any sea-insurance is made for or upon a voyage and also for time, or to extend to or cover any time beyond thirty days after the ship shall have arrived at her destination and been there moored at anchor, the policy shall be charged with duty as a policy for or upon a voyage, and also with duty as a policy for time.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (45485)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Bonds, debentures or other securities issued on loans under Act XI of 1879.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 1910, s. 2, for "eight annas per centum".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45485&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything in this Act, any local authority raising a loan under the provisions of the`
  line `Local Authorities Loan Act, 1879 (XI of 1879) or, of any other law for the time being in force, by the`
  line `issue of bonds, debentures or other securities, shall, in respect of such loan, be chargeable with a duty of`
  line ^1
  line `[one per centum] on the total amount of the bonds, debentures or other securities issued by it, and such`
  line `bonds, debentures or other securities need not be stamped and shall not be chargeable with any further`
  line `duty on renewal, consolidation, sub-division or otherwise.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) exempting certain bonds, debentures or other securities from`
  line `being stamped and from being chargeable with certain further duty shall apply to the bonds, debentures or`
  line `other securities of all outstanding loans of the kind mentioned therein, and all such bonds, debentures or`
  line `other securities shall be valid, whether the same are stamped or not:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing herein contained shall exempt the local authority which has issued such bonds,`
  line `debentures or other securities from the duty chargeable in respect thereof prior to the twenty-sixth day of`
  line `March, 1897, when such duty has not already been paid or remitted by order issued by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) In the case of wilful neglect to pay the duty required by this section, the local authority shall be`
  line `liable to forfeit to the Government a sum equal to ten per centum upon the amount of duty payable, and a`
  line `like penalty for every month after the first month during which the neglect continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_a:
  sectionId (45486)
  sectionNo 8A
  orderNo 10
  title `Securities dealt in depository not liable to stamp-duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 14, for section 8A (w.e.f. 1-4-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45486&sectionno=8A&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[8A. Securities dealt in depository not liable to stamp duty.---Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act or any other law for the time being in force,---`
  line
  line `(a) an issuer, by the issue of securities to one or more depositories, shall, in respect of such issue,`
  line `be chargeable with duty on the total amount of securities issued by it and such securities need not be`
  line stamped;
  line
  line `(b) the transfer of registered ownership of securities from a person to a depository or from a`
  line `depository to a beneficial owner shall not be liable to duty;`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this section, the expression "beneficial ownership" shall have the`
  line `same meaning as assigned to it in clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Depositories Act, 1996`
  line `(22 of 1996)]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_b:
  sectionId (45487)
  sectionNo 8B
  orderNo 11
  title `Corporatisation and demutualisation schemes and related instruments not liable to duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2005, s.114 (w.e.f. 13-5-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45487&sectionno=8B&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_8_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[8B. Corporatisation and demutualisation schemes and related instruments not liable to`
  line `duty---Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or any other law for the time being in force,--`
  line
  line `(a) a scheme for corporatisation or demutualisation, or both of a recognised stock exchange; or`
  line
  line `(b) any instrument, including an instrument of, or relating to, transfer of any property, business,`
  line `asset whether movable or immovable, contract, right, liability and obligation, for the purpose of, or in`
  line `connection with, the corporatisation or demutualisation, or both of a recognised stock exchange`
  line `pursuant to a scheme,`
  line
  line `as approved by the Securities and Exchange Board of India under sub-section (2) of section 4B of the`
  line `Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956), shall not be liable to duty under this Act or any`
  line `other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) the expressions "corporatisation", "demutualisation" and "scheme" shall have the meanings`
  line `respectively assigned to them in clauses (aa), (ab) and (ga) of section 2 of the Securities Contracts`
  line `(Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(b) "Securities and Exchange Board of India" means the Securities and Exchange Board of India`
  line `established under section 3 of the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992).]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_c:
  sectionId (45488)
  sectionNo 8C
  orderNo 12
  title `Negotiable warehouse receipts not liable to stamp duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins by Act 37 of 2007, s. 55 (w.e.f. 25-10-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45488&sectionno=8C&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_8_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[8C. Negotiable warehouse receipts not liable to stamp-duty.--Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act, negotiable warehouse receipts shall not be liable to stamp duty.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_d:
  sectionId (45489)
  sectionNo 8D
  orderNo 13
  title `Agreement or document for assignment of receivables not liable to stamp duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 12 of 2012, s. 35 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1-2-2012).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45489&sectionno=8D&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_8_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[8D. Agreement or document for assignment of receivables not liable to stamp-duty. --Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or any other law for the time being in force, any`
  line `agreement or other document for assignment of receivables as defined in clause (p) of section 2 of the`
  line `Factoring Regulation Act, 2011 in favour of any factor as defined in clause (i) of section 2 of the said`
  line `Act shall not be liable to duty under this Act or any other law for the time being in force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_e:
  sectionId (45569)
  sectionNo 8E
  orderNo 14
  title `Conversion of a branch of any bank into a wholly owned subsidiary of bank or transfer of shareholding of a bank to a holding company of bank not liable to duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 2013, s. 17 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 17-1-2013).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45569&sectionno=8E&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_8_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[8E. Conversion of a branch of any bank into a wholly owned subsidiary of bank or transfer of`
  line `shareholding of a bank to a holding company of bank not liable to duty. ---Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act or any other law for the time being in force,--`
  line
  line `(a) conversion of a branch of a bank into a wholly owned subsidiary of the bank or transfer of`
  line `shareholding of a bank to a holding company of the bank in terms of the scheme or guidelines of the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India shall not be liable to duty under this Act or any other law for the time being in`
  line `force; or`
  line
  line `(b) any instrument, including an instrument of, or relating to, transfer of any property, business,`
  line `asset whether movable or immovable, contract, right, liability and obligation, for the purpose of, or in`
  line `connection with, the conversion of a branch of a bank into a wholly owned subsidiary of the bank or`
  line `transfer of shareholding of a bank to a holding company of the bank in terms of the scheme or`
  line `guidelines issued by the Reserve Bank of India in this behalf, shall not be liable to duty under this Act`
  line `or any other law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line Explanation.--
  line
  line `(i) For the purposes of this section, the expression bank means--`
  line
  line `(a) "a banking company" as defined in clause (c) of section 5 of the Banking Regulation Act,`
  line `1949 (10 of 1949);`
  line
  line `(b) "a corresponding new bank" as defined in clause (da) of section 5 of the Banking`
  line `Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949);`
  line
  line `(c) "State Bank of India' constituted under section 3 of the State Bank of India Act, 1955 (23`
  line `of 1955);`
  line
  line `(d) "a subsidiary bank" as defined in clause (k) of section 2 of the State Bank of India`
  line `(Subsidiary Banks) Act, 1959 (38 of 1959);`
  line
  line `(e) "a Regional Rural Bank" established under section 3 of the Regional Rural Banks Act,`
  line `1976 (21 of 1976);`
  line
  line `(f) "a Co-operative Bank" as defined in clause (cci) of section 5 of the Banking Regulation`
  line `Act, 1949 (10 of 1949);`
  line
  line `(g) "a multi-State co-operative bank" as defined in clause (cciiia) of section 5 of the Banking`
  line `Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949);`
  line
  line `(ii) For the purposes of this section, the expression the Reserve Bank of India means the`
  line `Reserve Bank of India constituted under section 3 of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of`
  line `1934).]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_f:
  sectionId (45570)
  sectionNo 8F
  orderNo 15
  title `Agreement or document for transfer or assignment of rights or interest in financial assets not liable to stamp duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 44 of 2016, s. 43 and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 1-9-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45570&sectionno=8F&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_8_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[8F. Agreement or document for transfer or assignment of rights or interest in financial assets`
  line `not liable to stamp-duty.---Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, any agreement or other document for transfer or assignment of rights or interest in`
  line `financial assets of banks or financial institutions under section 5 of the Securitisation and Reconstruction`
  line `of Financial Assets and Enforcement of Security Interest Act, 2002 (54 of 2002), in favour of any asset reconstruction`
  line `company, as defined in clause (ba) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of that Act, shall not be liable to duty`
  line `under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_g:
  sectionId (56398)
  sectionNo 8G
  orderNo 16
  title `Strategic sale, disinvestment, etc., of immovable property by Government company not liable to stamp duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_g_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 126 (w.e.f. 28-3-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=56398&sectionno=8G&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_8_g_content:
  string
  line `^1[8G. Strategic sale, disinvestment, etc., of immovable property by Government company not`
  line `liable to stamp duty.—Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, any instrument for conveyance or transfer of a business or asset or right in any immovable`
  line `property from a Government company, its subsidiary, unit or joint venture,`
  line `(i) by way of strategic sale or disinvestment or demerger or any other scheme of arrangements or`
  line `through any law, to another Government company or to the Central Government or any State`
  line `Government or to the development financial institution established by any law made by Parliament;`
  line or
  line
  line `(ii) which is to be wound up, closed, struck-off, liquidated or otherwise shut down, to another`
  line `Government company or to the Central Government or any State Government,`
  line `after approval of the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, shall not be liable`
  line `to duty under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, “Government company” shall have the same meaning`
  line `as assigned to it in clause (45) of section 2 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013).]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (45492)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power to reduce, remit or compound duties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45492&sectionno=9&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] ^2[The ^3***Government] may, by rule or`
  line `order published in the Official Gazette,--`
  line
  line `(a) reduce or remit, whether prospectively or retrospectively, in the whole or any part of ^4[the`
  line `territories under its administration, the duties with which any instruments or any particular class of`
  line `instruments, or any of the instruments belonging to such class, or any instruments when executed by`
  line `or in favour of any particular class of persons, or by or in favour of any members of such class, are`
  line `chargeable, and`
  line
  line `(b) provide for the composition or consolidation of duties ^5[of policies of insurance and] in the`
  line `case of issues by any incorporated company or other body corporate ^6[or of transfers (where there is a`
  line `single transferee, whether incorporated or not)] of debentures, bond or other marketable securities.`
  line
  line `^7[(2) In this section the expression "the Government" means,--`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to stamp-duty in respect of bills of exchange, cheques, promissory notes, bills of`
  line `lading, letters of credit, policies of insurance, transfer of shares, debentures, proxies and receipts, and`
  line `in relation to any other stamp-duty chargeable under this Act and falling within entry 96 in List I in`
  line `the ^8[Seventh Schedule to the Constitution, expect the subject matters referred to in clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1)]; the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) Save as aforesaid, the State Government.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka--
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 9A.--After section 9 of the Indian Stamp Act, 1899 (Central Act 2 of 1899), the following section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"9A. Power of State Government to consolidate duties in respect of receipts.--Subject to`
  line `such conditions as may be specified, the State Government may, by order, provide for the`
  line `consolidation of duties in respect of any receipts or class of receipts given by any person or class of`
  line `persons including any Government."`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 29 of 1978, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. S. 9 re-numbered as sub-section (1) of that section by the A.O. 1950.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for the G.G. in C.`
  line
  line `3. The word collecting omitted by the A.O. 1950.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for British India.`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 117.`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 99 (w.e.f. 13-9-1994).`
  line
  line `7. Added by the A.O. 1950.`
  line
  line `8. Subs by Act 21 of 2006 s. 69, for Seventh Schedule to the Constitution. (w.e.f. 18-4-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_a:
  sectionId (49724)
  sectionNo 9A
  orderNo 18
  title `Instruments chargeable with duty for transactions in stock exchanges and depositories.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=49724&sectionno=9A&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[9A. Instruments chargeable with duty for transactions in stock exchanges and depositories.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) when the sale of any securities, whether delivery based or otherwise, is made through a stock`
  line `exchange, the stamp-duty on each such sale in the clearance list shall be collected on behalf of the`
  line `State Government by the stock exchange or a clearing corporation authorised by it, from its buyer on`
  line `the market value of such securities at the time of settlement of transactions in securities of such buyer,`
  line `in such manner as the Central Government may, by rules, provide;`
  line
  line `(b) when any transfer of securities for a consideration, whether delivery based or otherwise, is`
  line `made by a depository otherwise than on the basis of any transaction referred to in clause (a), the`
  line `stamp-duty on such transfer shall be collected on behalf of the State Government by the depository`
  line `from the transferor of such securities on the consideration amount specified therein, in such manner`
  line `as the Central Government may, by rules, provide;`
  line
  line `(c) when pursuant to issue of securities, any creation or change in the records of a depository is`
  line `made, the stamp-duty on the allotment list shall be collected on behalf of the State Government by the`
  line `depository from the issuer of securities on the total market value of the securities as contained in such`
  line `list, in such manner as the Central Government may, by rules, provide.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the instruments referred to in sub-section (1) shall`
  line `be chargeable with duty as provided therein at the rate specified in Schedule I and such instruments need`
  line `not be stamped.`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that no such duty shall be chargeable in respect of the instruments of transaction in stock`
  line `exchanges and depositories established in any International Financial Services Centre set up under`
  line `section 18 of the Special Economic Zones Act, 2005 (28 of 2005).]`
  line
  line `(3) From the date of commencement of this Part, no stamp-duty shall be charged or collected by the`
  line `State Government on any note or memorandum or any other document, electronic or otherwise,`
  line `associated with the transactions mentioned in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) The stock exchange or a clearing corporation authorised by it or the depository, as the case may`
  line `be, shall, within three weeks of the end of each month and in accordance with the rules made in this`
  line `behalf by the Central Government, in consultation with the State Government, transfer the stamp-duty`
  line `collected under this section to the State Government where the residence of the buyer is located and in`
  line `case the buyer is located outside India, to the State Government having the registered office of the trading`
  line `member or broker of such buyer and in case where there is no such trading member of the buyer, to the`
  line `State Government having the registered office of the participant:`
  line
  line `Provided that before such transfer, the stock exchange or the clearing corporation authorised by it or`
  line `the depository shall be entitled to deduct such percentage of stamp-duty towards facilitation charges as`
  line `may be specified in such rules.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The term participant shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (g) of`
  line `section 2 of the Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996).`
  line
  line `(5) Every stock exchange or the clearing corporation authorised by it and depository shall submit to`
  line `the Government details of the transactions referred to in sub-section (1) in such manner as the Central`
  line `Government may, by rules, provide.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-7-2020). [Earlier notified w.e.f. 9-1-2020 followed by 1-4-2020.]`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 12 of 2020, s. 143, (w.e.f. 1-4-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_b:
  sectionId (49725)
  sectionNo 9B
  orderNo 19
  title `Instruments chargeable with duty for transactions otherwise than through stock exchanges and depositories.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=49725&sectionno=9B&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_9_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[9B. Instruments chargeable with duty for transactions otherwise than through stock exchanges`
  line `and depositories.--Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) when any issue of securities is made by an issuer otherwise than through a stock exchange or`
  line `depository, the stamp-duty on each such issue shall be payable by the issuer, at the place where its`
  line `registered office is located, on the total market value of the securities so issued at the rate specified in`
  line `Schedule I;`
  line
  line `(b) when any sale or transfer or reissue of securities for consideration is made otherwise than`
  line `through a stock exchange or depository, the stamp-duty on each such sale or transfer or reissue shall`
  line `be payable by the seller or transferor or issuer, as the case may be, on the consideration amount`
  line `specified in such instrument at the rate specified in Schedule I.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (45571)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 20
  title `Duties how to be paid.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45571&sectionno=10&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except as otherwise expressly provided in this Act, all duties with`
  line `which any instruments are chargeable shall be paid, and such payment shall be indicated on such`
  line `instruments, by means of stamps--`
  line
  line `(a) according to the provisions herein contained; or`
  line
  line `(b) when no such provision is applicable thereto0--as the ^1[State Government] may be rule direct.`
  line
  line `(2) The rules made under sub-section (1) may, among other matters, regulate,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of each kind of instrument--the description of stamps which may be used;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of instruments stamped with impressed stamps--the number of stamps which may`
  line `be used;`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of bills of exchange or promissory notes ^2*** the size of the paper on which they`
  line `are written.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Assam--
  line
  line `Insertion of section 10A.--The principal Act, after the existing section the following shall be`
  line `inserted as section 10A, namely:--`
  line
  line `"10A. For shortage of stamps how duty to be paid--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `Section 10, where the State Government or the Collector, as the case may be, is satisfied that there is`
  line `shortage of stamps in the district or stamps of required denominations are not available, the State`
  line `Government or the Collector may permit payment of the duty to be paid in cash or by way of Demand`
  line `Draft or by Pay Order and authorize the Treasury Officer or Sub-Treasury Officer or Sub-Registrar or`
  line `any other authorised officer, as the case may be, on production of a challan evidencing payment of`
  line `duty in the Government Treasury or Sub-Treasury of a Demand Draft or by Pay Order drawn on a`
  line `branch of any Schedule bank, as the case may be, after due verification, to certify in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed, by endorsement on the instrument of the amount of duty so paid in cash.aid in cash.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Government Treasury includes a Government Sub-Treasury and any other place`
  line `as the State Government may, by notification in the Assam Gazette, appoint in this behalf:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may, be order published in the Official Gazette, direct that`
  line `the power exercisable by it or by the Collector under this Section may be exercised by such other`
  line `officers as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(2) An endorsement made on any instrument under sub-section (1) shall have the same effect as if`
  line `the duty of an amount equal to the amount stated in the endorsement has been paid in respect thereof`
  line `and such payment has been indicated on such instrument by means of stamps in accordance with the`
  line `requirements of section 10.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall apply to,--`
  line
  line `(i) the payment of stamp duty chargeable on the instruments specified in Entry 91 of List I of`
  line `the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution of India; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the instruments presented after six months from the date of their execution or first`
  line `execution."`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 22 of 2004, s. 2]`
  line
  line Meghalaya--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 10 of Central act 2 of 1899.--In the Indian Stamp Act, 1899 after section 10`
  line `the following new section shall be inserted as section 10A, namely:--`
  line
  line `"10A. Notwithstanding anything contained in section 10 where,`
  line
  line `(a) (i) The State Government, in relation to any area in the State; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the Deputy Commissioner, in relation to any area in District under his charge, is satisfied`
  line `that on account of temporary, shortage of stamps in any area, duty cannot be paid, and payment`
  line `of duty cannot be indicated on instruments, by means of Stamps, the State Government, or as the`
  line `case may be, the Deputy Commissioner may, by notification, in the Official Gazette, direct that in`
  line `such area and for such period as maybe specified in such notification, the duty may be paid in`
  line `cash in any Treasury or Sub-Treasury and shall on production of a challan evidencing payments`
  line `of stamp duty in the Government treasury certify endorsement on the instrument in respect of`
  line `which the stamp duty is paid, that the duty has been paid, and state in the said endorsement the`
  line `amount of the duty so paid.`
  line
  line `(b) An endorsement made on any instrument under clause (a) shall have the same effect as if`
  line `the duty of an amount equal to the amount stated in the endorsement had been paid in respect of,`
  line `and such payment has been indicated on, such instrument by means of stamps, under section 10.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Meghalaya Act 6 of 1973, s.2]`
  line
  line Uttarakhand--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 10.--After section 10(A) the following section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `10(B) "Various modes of payment of duty" Notwithstanding anything contained in section 10 &`
  line `10(A) all duties with which any instruments are chargeable shall be paid,--`
  line
  line `(1) by way of cash; or`
  line
  line `(2) by demand draft; or`
  line
  line `(3) by pay order; or`
  line
  line `(4) by e-payment;`
  line
  line `in Government Treasury or Sub-Treasury or General Stamp Office or, as the case may be,`
  line `Government Receipt Accounting System (G.R.A.S.) (Virtual Treasury) and such payment shall be`
  line `indicated by endorsement on such instruments by an officer authorised by the State Government.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 1 of 2016, s. 3]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 10-A.— In section 10-A of the Principal Act, for sub-section (1) the following`
  line `sub-section shall be substituted namely :—`
  line
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 10—`
  line
  line `(a) where the Collector is satisfied that there is temporary shortage of stamps in the district or that`
  line `stamps of required denominations are not available, he may permit duty to be paid in cash and`
  line `authorize the officer-in-charge of the treasury on production of a challan evidencing payment of duty`
  line `in the Government treasury or sub-treasury, to certify by endorsement on the instrument or`
  line `instruments the amount of duty so paid in cash ;`
  line
  line `(b) where the State Government considers it expedient so to do, it may, in any district, permit`
  line `duty to be paid in cash and authorize any officer, to receive payment of duty in cash and to certify by`
  line `endorsement by means of a Franking machine on the instrument or instruments the amount of duty so`
  line `paid in cash.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 11 of 1992, s. 3]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 10-A.— After section 10 of the principal Act, the following section shall be`
  line `inserted, namely :—`
  line
  line `“10-A. Payment of duty in cash.—(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 10, where`
  line `the Collector is satisfied that there is temporary shortage of stamps in the district or that stamps of`
  line `required denominations are not available, he may permit duty to be paid in cash and authorize the`
  line `officer-in-charge of the treasury on production of a challan evidencing payment of duty in the`
  line `Government treasury or sub-treasury, to certify by endorsement on the instruments or instruments the`
  line `amount of duty so paid in cash.`
  line
  line `(2) An endorsement made on any instrument under sub-section (1) shall have the same effect as if`
  line `the duty of an amount equal to the amount stated in the endorsement has been paid in respect thereof`
  line `and such payment has been indicated on such instrument by means of stamps in accordance with the`
  line `requirement of section 10.”`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 20 of 1974, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "collecting Government".`
  line
  line `2. The words "written in any oriental language" omitted by Act 43 of 1955, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (45494)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 21
  title `Use of adhesive stamps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45494&sectionno=11&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The following instruments may be stamped with adhesive stamps,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) instruments chargeable ^1[with a duty not exceeding ten naye paise], except parts of bills of`
  line `exchange payable otherwise than on demand and drawn in sets;`
  line
  line `(b) bills of exchange, ^2*** and promissory notes drawn or made out of ^3[India];`
  line
  line `(c) entry as an advocate, vakil or attorney on the roll of a High Court;`
  line `(d) notarial acts; and`
  line
  line `(e) transfers by endorsement of shares in any incorporated company or other body corporate.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 11.--In section 11 of the principal Act, in clause (c), after the words "State Bar`
  line `Council of Uttar Pradesh " the words and certificates of enrolment issued to Revenue Agents or`
  line `Mukhtars" shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 19 of 1982, s. 3]`
  line
  line `Insertion of section 11-A.— After section 11 of the principal Act, the following section shall be`
  line `inserted, namely :—.`
  line
  line `“11-A. Payment of duty in cash on such memos.— (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 11, the stamp duty due under Article 25-A of Schedule I-B on a counterpart or duplicate`
  line `(including counterfoil or carbon copy) of a bill or cash memo may be paid either by means of stamps`
  line `on the date of issue of such instruments, or in cash once in every quarter, for all such instruments`
  line `issued in the previous quarter, into the treasury or sub-treasury under such head as the State`
  line `Government may by general or special order direct..`
  line
  line `(2) The treasury challan prepared for deposit of duty in cash shall be accompanied by such`
  line `statement and shall be preserved for the purpose of verification for such period and proper account`
  line `thereof shall be maintained in such form as the State Government may by general or special order`
  line direct.”
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 49 of 1975, s. 4].`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 11.—In section 11 of the principal Act, in clause (c), after the words “State Bar`
  line `Council of Uttar Pradesh” the words “and certificate of enrolment issued to Revenue Agents or`
  line `Mukhtars” shall be inserted..`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 19 of 1981, s. 3].`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1958, s. 2, for with the duty of one anna or half an anna (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  line
  line `2. The word cheques omitted by Act 5 of 1927, s. 5.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 43 of 1955, s. 2, for the States (w.e.f. 1-4-1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (45495)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 22
  title `Cancellation of adhesive stamps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45495&sectionno=12&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) (a) Whoever affixes any adhesive stamp to any`
  line `instrument chargeable with duty which has been executed by any person shall, when affixing such stamp,`
  line `cancel the same so that it cannot be used again; and`
  line
  line `(b) whoever executes any instrument on any paper bearing an adhesive stamp shall, at the time of`
  line `execution, unless such stamp has been already cancelled in manner aforesaid, cancel the same so that it`
  line `cannot be used again.`
  line
  line `(2) Any instrument bearing an adhesive stamp which has not been cancelled so that it cannot be used`
  line `again, shall, so far as such stamp is concerned, be deemed to be unstamped.`
  line
  line `(3)The person required by sub-section (1) to cancel an adhesive stamp may cancel it by writing on or`
  line `across the stamp his name or initials or the name or initials of his firm with the true date of his so writing,`
  line `or in any other effectual manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (45496)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 23
  title `Instruments stamped with impressed stamps how to be written.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45496&sectionno=13&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Every instrument written`
  line `upon paper stamped with an impressed stamp shall be written in such manner that the stamp may appear`
  line `on the face of the instrument and cannot be used for or applied to any other instrument.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (45497)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 24
  title `Only one instrument to be on same stamps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45497&sectionno=14&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `No second instrument chargeable with duty shall`
  line `be written upon a piece of stamped paper upon which an instrument chargeable with duty has already`
  line `been written:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall prevent any endorsement which is duly stamped or is not`
  line `chargeable with duty being made upon any instrument for the purpose of transferring any right created or`
  line `evidenced thereby, or of acknowledging the receipt of any money or goods the payment or delivery of`
  line `which is secured thereby.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (45498)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 25
  title `Instrument written contrary to section 13 or 14 deemed unstamped.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45498&sectionno=15&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Every instrument`
  line `written in contravention of section 13 or section 14 shall be deemed to be unstamped.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (45499)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 26
  title `Denoting duty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "collecting Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45499&sectionno=16&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Where the duty with which an instrument is chargeable, or its exemption from`
  line `duty, depends in any manner upon the duty actually paid in respect of another instrument, the payment of`
  line `such last-mentioned duty shall, if application is made in writing to the Collector for that purpose, and on`
  line `production of both the instruments, be denoted upon such first-mentioned instrument by endorsement`
  line `under the hand of the Collector or in such other manner (if any) as the ^1[State Government] may by rule`
  line prescribe.
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (45572)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 27
  title `Instrument executed in India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 1955, s. 2, for "the States" (w.e.f. 1-4-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45572&sectionno=17&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `All instruments chargeable with duty and executed by any`
  line `person in ^1[India] shall be stamped before or at the time of execution.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Assam--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 17.--In the principal Act, in Section 17, after the existing provision, the`
  line `following proviso shall be inserted namely:--`
  line
  line `"Provided that nothing in this Section shall apply to the instrument in respect of which stamp duty has`
  line `been paid under section 10-A."`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 22 of 2004, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (45501)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 28
  title `Instruments other than bills and notes executed out of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45501&sectionno=18&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every instrument`
  line `chargeable with duty executed only out of ^2[India], and not being a bill of exchange ^3*** or promissory`
  line `note, may be stamped within three months after it has been first received in ^2[India].`
  line
  line `(2) Where any such instrument cannot, with reference to the description of stamp prescribed`
  line `therefore, be duly stamped by a private person, it may be taken within the said period of three months to`
  line `the Collector, who shall stamp the same, in such manner as the ^1[State Government] may by rule`
  line `prescribe, with a stamp of such value as the person so taking such instrument may require and pay for.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "collecting Government".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 43 of 1955, s. 2, for "the States" (w.e.f. 1-4-1956).`
  line
  line `3. The word "cheque" omitted by Act 5 of 1927, s. 5.`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (45502)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 29
  title `Bills and notes drawn out of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45502&sectionno=19&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The first holder in ^1[India] of any bill of`
  line `exchange ^3[payable otherwise than on demand], ^2*** or promissory note drawn or made out of ^1[India]`
  line `shall, before he presents the same for acceptance or payment, or endorses, transfers or otherwise`
  line `negotiates the same in ^1[India], affix thereto the proper stamp and cancel the same:`
  line
  line `Provided that,--`
  line
  line `(a) if, at the time any such bill of exchange,`
  line `^2*** or note comes into the hands of any holder`
  line `thereof in ^1[India], the proper adhesive stamp is affixed thereto and cancelled in manner prescribed by`
  line `section 12 and such holder has no reason to believe that such stamp was affixed or cancelled`
  line `otherwise than by the person and at the time required by this Act, such stamp shall, so far as relates to`
  line `such holder, be deemed to have been duly affixed and cancelled;`
  line
  line `(b) nothing contained in this proviso shall relieve any person from any penalty incurred by him`
  line `for omitting to affix or cancel a stamp.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Himachal Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Addition of a new section 19-A.--After section 19 of the said Act the following new section shall be inserted, namely:---`
  line
  line `19-A. Payment of duty on certain instruments liable to increased duty in Himachal Pradesh under clause (bb) of section 3.-- Where any instrument has become chargeable in any part of India and thereafter becomes chargeable with higher rate of duty in the Himachal Pradesh under clause (bb) of the first proviso to section 3 as amended by the Indian Stamp (Himachal Pradesh Amendment) Act, 1952--`
  line
  line `(i) notwithstanding anything contained in the said proviso, the amount of duty chargeable on such instrument shall be the amount chargeable on it under Schedule- I-A less the amount of duty, if any already paid on it in India,`
  line
  line `(ii) in addition to the stamps, if any, already affixed thereto, such instrument shall be stamped with the stamps necessary for the payment of the amount of duty chargeable on it under clause (i) in the same manner and at the same time and by the same person as though such instrument were an instrument received in India for the first time at the time when it became chargeable with the higher duty.`
  line
  line `[Vide Himachal Pradesh Act 4 of 1953, s. 7]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 1955, s. 2, for the States (w.e.f. 1-4-1956).`
  line
  line `2. The word cheque omitted by Act 5 of 1927, s. 5.`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 5, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (45575)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 30
  title `Conversion of amount expressed in foreign currencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 1955, s. 2, for "the States" (w.e.f. 1-4-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45575&sectionno=20&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an instrument is`
  line `chargeable with ad valorem duty in respect of any money expressed in any currency other than that of`
  line `^1[India] such duty shall be calculated on the value of such money in the currency of ^1[India] according to`
  line `the current rate of exchange on the day of the date of the instrument.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, from time to time, by notification in the Official Gazette, prescribe`
  line `a rate of exchange for the conversion of British or any foreign currency into the currency of ^1[India] for`
  line `the purposes of calculating stamp-duty, and such rate shall be deemed to be the current rate for the`
  line `purposes of sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (45504)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 31
  title `Stock and marketable securities how to be valued.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45504&sectionno=21&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Where an instrument is chargeable with`
  line `ad valorem duty in respect of any stock or of any marketable or other security, such duty shall be`
  line `calculated on ^1[the market value of such stock or security.]`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the market value for calculating the stamp-duty shall be, in the case of--`
  line
  line `(i) options in any securities, the premium paid by the buyer;`
  line
  line `(ii) repo on corporate bonds, interest paid by the borrower; and`
  line
  line `(iii) swap, only the first leg of the cash flow.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 16, for "the value of such stock or security according to the average price or the value thereof on the`
  line `day of the date of the instrument." (w.e.f. 1-4-2020).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 16, ibid.,(w.e.f. 1-4-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (45505)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 32
  title `Effect of statement of rate of exchange or average price.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45505&sectionno=22&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Where an instrument contains a`
  line `statement of current rate of exchange, or average price, as the case may require, and is stamped in`
  line `accordance with such statement, it shall, so far as regards the subject-matter of such statement, be`
  line `presumed, until the contrary is proved, to be duly stamped.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (45506)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 33
  title `Instruments reserving interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45506&sectionno=23&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Where interest is expressly made payable by the terms of an`
  line `instrument, such instrument shall not be chargeable with duty higher than that with which it would have`
  line `been chargeable had no mention of interest been made therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23_a:
  sectionId (45573)
  sectionNo 23A
  orderNo 34
  title `Certain instruments connected with mortgages of marketable securities to be chargeable as agreements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45573&sectionno=23A&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[23A. Certain instruments connected with mortgages of marketable securities to be chargeable`
  line `as agreements. --(1) Where an instrument (not being a promissory note or bill of exchange)--`
  line
  line `(a) is given upon the occasion of the deposit of any marketable security by way of security for`
  line `money advanced or to be advanced by way of loan, or for an existing or future debt, or`
  line
  line `(b) makes redeemable or qualifies a duly stamped transfer, intended as a security, of any`
  line `marketable security,`
  line
  line `it shall be chargeable with duty as if it were an agreement or memorandum of an agreement chargeable`
  line `with duty under ^2[Article No. 5 (c)] of Schedule I.`
  line
  line `(2) A release or discharge of any such instrument shall only be chargeable with the like duty.].`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Himachal Pradesh--`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 23-A.-- In sub-section (1) of section 23-A of the said Act, for the word and figure ‘Schedule-I’ the word, figure and letter “Schedule I-A” shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Himachal Pradesh Act 4 of 1953, s. 8]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 1904, s. 3.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 1 of 1912, s. 3, for "Article No. 5(b)".`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (45508)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 35
  title `How transfer in consideration of debt, or subject to future payment, etc., to be charged.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45508&sectionno=24&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Where any property is transferred to any person in consideration, wholly or in part, of any debt due to`
  line `him, or subject either certainly or contingently to the payment or transfer of any money or stock, whether`
  line `being or constituting a charge or incumbrance upon the property or not, such debt, money or stock is to be`
  line `deemed the whole or part, as the case may be, of the consideration in respect whereof the transfer is`
  line `chargeable with ad valorem duty:`
  line
  line `Provided that, nothing in this section shall apply to any such certificate of sale as is mentioned in`
  line `Article No. 18 of Schedule I.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- In the case of a sale of property subject to a mortgage or other incumbrance, any`
  line `unpaid mortgage-money or money charged, together with the interest (if any) due on the same, shall be`
  line `deemed to be part of the consideration for the sale:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where property subject to a mortgage is transferred to the mortgage, he shall be entitled`
  line `to deduct from the duty payable on the transfer the amount of any duty already paid in respect of the`
  line mortgage.
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(1) A owes B Rs. 1,000. A sells a property to B, the consideration being Rs. 500 and the release of the`
  line `previous debt of Rs. 1,000. Stamp-duty is payable on Rs. 1,500.`
  line
  line `(2) A sells a property to B for Rs. 500 which is subject to a mortgagee to C for Rs. 1,000 and unpaid`
  line `interest Rs 200. Stamp-duty is payable on Rs. 1,700.`
  line
  line `(3) A mortgages a house of the value of Rs. 10,000 to B for Rs. 5,000. B afterwards buys the house`
  line `from A. Stamp-duty is payable on Rs. 10,000 less the amount of stamp-duty already paid for the`
  line mortgage.
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Himachal Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 24.--- In the proviso to section 24, of the said Act, for the full stop shall be substituted a comma followed by the words "or Schedule I -A, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `[Vide Himachal Pradesh Act 4 of 1953, s. 9]`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 24.-- In Section 24 of the Indian Stamp Act, 1899 (2 of 1899) (herein after`
  line `referred to as the principal Act), for the words "in respect whereof the transfer is chargeable with ad`
  line `valorem duty" the words "and the transfer is chargeable with ad valorem duty in respect of the`
  line `consideration or the market value of the property so transferred, whichever is higher," shall be`
  line substituted.
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 7 of 1987, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (45509)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 36
  title `Valuation in case of annuity, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45509&sectionno=25&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Where an instrument is executed to secure the payment of`
  line `an annuity or other sum payable periodically, or where the consideration for a conveyance is an annuity`
  line `or other sum payable periodically, the amount secured by such instrument or the consideration for such`
  line `conveyance, as the case may be, shall, for the purposes of this Act, be deemed to be,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the sum is payable for a definite period so that the total amount to be paid can be`
  line `previously ascertained---such total amount;`
  line
  line `(b) where the sum is payable in perpetuity or for an indefinite time not terminable with any life in`
  line `being at the date of such instrument or conveyance----the total amount which, according to the terms`
  line `of such instrument or conveyance, will or may be payable during the period of twenty years`
  line `calculated from the date on which the first payment becomes due; and`
  line
  line `(c) where the sum is payable for an indefinite time terminable with any life in being at the date of`
  line `such instrument or conveyance---- the maximum amount which will or may be payable as aforesaid`
  line `during the period of twelve years calculated from the date on which the first payment becomes due.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (45510)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 37
  title `Stamp where value of subject-matter is indeterminate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45510&sectionno=26&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Where the amount or value of the`
  line `subject-matter of any instrument chargeable with ad valorem duty cannot be, or (in the case of an`
  line `instrument executed before the commencement of this Act) could not have been, ascertained at the date of`
  line `its execution or first execution, nothing shall be claimable under such instrument more than the highest`
  line `amount or value for which, if stated in an instrument of the same description, the stamp actually used`
  line `would, at the date of such execution, have been sufficient:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that, in the case of the lease of a mine in which royalty or a share of the produce is`
  line `received as the rent or part of the rent, it shall be sufficient to have estimated such royalty or the value of`
  line `such share, for the purpose of stamp-duty,`
  line
  line `(a) when the lease has been granted by or on behalf of`
  line `^2[the Government], at such amount or`
  line `value as the Collector may, having regard to all the circumstances of the case, have estimated as`
  line `likely to be payable by way of royalty or share to ^3[the Government under the lease, or`
  line
  line `(b) when the lease has been granted by any other person, at twenty thousand rupees a year,`
  line
  line `and the whole amount of such royalty or share, whatever it may be, shall be claimable under such lease:]`
  line
  line `Provided also that where proceedings have been taken in respect of an instrument under section 31 or`
  line `41, the amount certified by the Collector shall be deemed to be the stamp actually used at the date of`
  line execution.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1904, s. 4, for the proviso.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "the secretary of State in Council".`
  line
  line `3. Subs., ibid., for "the said Secretary of State in Council".`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (45511)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 38
  title `Facts affecting duty to be set forth in instrument.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45511&sectionno=27&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The consideration (if any) and all other`
  line `facts and circumstances affecting the chargeability of any instrument with duty, or the amount of the duty`
  line `with which it its chargeable, shall be fully and truly set forth therein.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Assam--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 27.--In the principal Act, in section 27, for the words and brackets, "The`
  line `consideration (if any)", the words "the market value of the property" shall be substituted."`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 22 of 2004, s. 4]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 27.--In the principal Act, after section 27, the following new section shall be`
  line `inserted namely:--`
  line
  line `"27A. Instrument of conveyance etc. under valued how to be dealt with.--(1) If the`
  line `Registering Officer appointed under the Registration Act, 1908 (Central Act 16 of 1908) while`
  line `registering any instrument of conveyance, exchange or gift has reason to believe that the market value`
  line `of the property as fixed by the Government/Collector of the district, which is subject matter of`
  line `conveyance, exchange or gift had not been truly set forth in the instrument, he may after registering`
  line `such instrument, refer the same to the Collector for determination of the market value of such proper`
  line `and the property duty payable thereon.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of a reference under sub-section (1), the Collector shall, after giving the parties a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard and after holding an enquiry in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by rules made under this Act, determine the market value of the property which is the`
  line `subject matter of conveyance, exchange or gift and the duty as aforesaid, and thereupon the`
  line `difference, if any, in the amount of duty, shall be payable by the persons liable to pay the duty.`
  line
  line `(3) The Collector may, on his own motion or otherwise, within two years from the date of`
  line `registration of any instrument or conveyance, exchange or gift not already referred to him under`
  line `sub-section (1) call for and examine the instrument for the purpose of satisfying himself as to the`
  line `correctness of the market value of the property as set forth in such instrument, which is the subject`
  line `matter of conveyance, exchange or gift and the duty payable thereon and if after such examination he`
  line `has reason to believe that the market value of such property has not been truly set forth in the`
  line `instrument, he may determine the market value of such property and the duty as aforesaid and`
  line `thereupon the difference, if any in the amount of duty, shall be payable by the person liable to pay the`
  line `duty:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to instrument registered before the date of`
  line `commencement of the Indian Stamp (Assam Amendment) Act, 2004.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person aggrieved by an order of the Collector under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3)`
  line `may prefer an appeal to the Civil Judge of appropriate jurisdiction and all such appeals shall be`
  line `preferred within such time and shall be heard and disposed of in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation--For the purpose of this Act, market value of any property shall be estimated to be`
  line `the price which in the opinion of the Collector or the Civil Judge Senior Division, as the case may be,`
  line `such property would have fetched or would fetch, if sold in the open market on the date of execution`
  line `of the instrument of conveyance, exchange or gift.`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 22 of 2004, s. 5]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Himachal Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 27.--For the words and brackets "The consideration (if any)" occurring in section 27 of the Indian Stamp Act, 1899 (2 of 1899) (hereinafter called as the principal Act), the words and signs "The consideration, if any, the market value of the property" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Himachal Pradesh Act 7 of 1989, s. 2]`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 27.-- In Section 27 of the principal Act, for the words and brackets`
  line `"the consideration if any", the words and commas "the consideration, if any, the market value of`
  line `the property" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 7 of 1987, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (45512)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 39
  title `Direction as to duty in case of certain conveyances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45512&sectionno=28&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any property has been`
  line `contracted to be sold for one consideration for the whole, and is conveyed to the purchaser in separate`
  line `parts by different instruments, the consideration shall be apportioned in such manner as the parties think`
  line `fit, provided that a distinct consideration for each separate part is set forth in the conveyance relating`
  line `thereto, and such conveyance shall be chargeable with ad valorem duty in respect of such distinct`
  line consideration.
  line
  line `(2) Where property contracted to be purchased for one consideration for the whole, by two or more`
  line `persons jointly, or by any person for himself and others, or wholly for others, is conveyed in parts by`
  line `separate instruments to the persons by or for whom the same was purchased, for distinct parts of the`
  line `consideration, the conveyance of each separate part shall be chargeable with ad valorem duty in respect of`
  line `the distinct part of the consideration therein specified.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a person, having contracted for the purchase of any property but not having obtained a`
  line `conveyance thereof, contracts to sell the same to any other person and the property is in consequence`
  line `conveyed immediately to the sub-purchaser the conveyance shall be chargeable with ad valorem duty in`
  line `respect of the consideration for the sale by the original purchaser to the sub-purchaser.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a person, having contracted for the purchase of any property but not having obtained a`
  line `conveyance thereof, contracts to sell the whole, or any part thereof, to any other person or persons and the`
  line `property is in consequence conveyed by the original seller to different persons in parts, the conveyance of`
  line `each part sold to a sub-purchaser shall be chargeable with ad valorem duty in respect only of the`
  line `consideration paid by such sub-purchaser, without regard to the amount or value of the original`
  line `consideration; and the conveyance of the residue (if any) of such property to the original purchaser shall`
  line `be chargeable with ad valorem duty in respect only of the excess of the original consideration over the`
  line `aggregate of the considerations paid by the sub-purchasers:`
  line
  line `Provided that the duty on such last-mentioned conveyance shall in no case be less than one rupee.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a sub-purchaser takes an actual conveyance of the interest of the person immediately`
  line `selling to him, which is chargeable with ad valorem duty in respect of the consideration paid by him and`
  line `is duly stamped accordingly, any conveyance to be afterwards made to him of the same property by the`
  line `original seller shall be chargeable with a duty equal to that which would be chargeable on a conveyance`
  line `for the consideration obtained by such original seller, or, where such duty would exceed five rupees, with`
  line `a duty of five rupees.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 28.-- In Section 28 of the principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(i) for sub-section (1), the following sub-section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(1) where any property has been contracted to be sold for one consideration for the whole, and is`
  line `conveyed to the purchaser in separate parts by different instruments, the consideration shall be`
  line `apportioned in such manner as the parties think fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that a distinct consideration for each separate part is set forth in the conveyance relating`
  line `thereto and such conveyance shall be chargeable with ad valorem duty in respect of such distinct`
  line `consideration:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the market value of the separate part shall be set forth along with the`
  line `consideration for each part and the conveyance shall be chargeable with ad valorem.`
  line
  line `[duty in respect of such distinct consideration or the market value, whichever is higher.".`
  line
  line `(ii) to sub-section (2) the following words and comma shall be added at the end, namely:--`
  line
  line `"or the market value of each such separate part whichever is higher.".`
  line
  line `(iii) to sub-section (3) the following words and comma shall be added at the end, namely:--`
  line
  line `"or the market value of the property, whichever is higher.".`
  line
  line `(iv) for sub-section (4), the following sub-section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(4) where a person, having contracted for the purchase of any property but not having obtained a`
  line `conveyance thereof, contracts to sell the whole, or any part thereof, to any other person or persons and`
  line `the property is in consequence conveyed by the original seller to different persons in part, the`
  line `conveyance of each part sold to a sub-purchaser shall be chargeable with ad valorem duty in respect`
  line `of the consideration paid by such sub-purchaser or the market value of each part whichever is higher`
  line `without regard to the amount or value of the original consideration; and the conveyance of the residue,`
  line `if any, of such property to the original purchaser shall be chargeable with ad valorem duty in respect`
  line `only of the excess of the original consideration over the aggregate of the considerations paid by the`
  line `sub-purchasers or the market value of the residue of such property whichever is higher:`
  line
  line `Provided that the duty on such last mentioned conveyance shall in no case be less than one rupee.".`
  line
  line `(v) for sub-section (5), the following sub-section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(5) Where a sub-purchaser takes an actual conveyance of the interest of the person immediately`
  line `selling to him, which is chargeable with ad valorem duty in respect of consideration paid by him or the`
  line `market value of the property whichever is higher and is duly stamped accordingly, any conveyance to be`
  line `afterwards made to him of the same property by the original seller shall be chargeable with a duty`
  line `equal to that which would be chargeable on a conveyance for the consideration obtained by such original seller or the market value of such property whichever is higher, or, where such duty would`
  line `exceed five rupees with a duty of five rupees",]`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 7 of 1987, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (45574)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 40
  title `Duties by whom payable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45574&sectionno=29&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `In the absence of an agreement to the contrary, the expense of`
  line `providing the proper stamp shall be borne --`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of any instrument described in any of the following Articles of Schedule I, namely:--`
  line
  line `No. 2. (Administration Bond),`
  line
  line `^1[No. 6 (Agreement relating to Deposit of Title-deeds, Pawn or Pledge),]`
  line
  line `No. 13 (Bill of exchange),`
  line
  line `No. 15 (Bond),`
  line
  line `No. 16 (Bottomry Bond),`
  line
  line `No. 26 (Customs Bond),`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `No. 32 (Further charge),`
  line
  line `No. 34 (Indemnity-Bond),`
  line
  line `No. 40 (Mortgage-deed),`
  line
  line `No. 49 (Promissory-note),`
  line
  line `No. 55 (Release),`
  line
  line `No. 56 (Respondentia Bond),`
  line
  line `No. 57 (Security-bond or Mortgage-deed),`
  line
  line `No. 58 (Settlement),`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `No. 62 (c). (Transfer of any interest secured by a bond, mortgage-deed or policy of insurance),--`
  line
  line `by the person drawing, making or executing such instrument:`
  line
  line `^5[(b) in the case of a policy of insurance other than fire-insurance---by the person effecting the`
  line insurance;
  line
  line `(bb) in the case of a policy of fire-insurance--by the person issuing the policy;]`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of a conveyance (including re-conveyance of mortgaged property) by the grantee: in`
  line `the case of a lease or agreement to lease---by the lessee or intended lessee:`
  line
  line `(d) in the case of a counterpart of a lease---by the lessor;`
  line
  line `(e) in the case of an instrument of exchange ^6[including swap]--by the parties in equal shares,`
  line
  line `(f) in the case of a certificate of sale---by the purchaser of the property to which such certificate`
  line `relates; ^7***`
  line
  line `(g) in the case of an instrument of partition---by the parties thereto in proportion to their respective`
  line `shares in the whole property partitioned or, when the partition is made in execution of an order passed by`
  line `a Revenue-authority or Civil Court or arbitrator, in such proportion as such authority, Court or arbitrator`
  line directs.
  line
  line `^8[(h) in the case of sale of security through stock exchange, by the buyer of such security;`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of sale of security otherwise than through a stock exchange, by the seller of such`
  line security;
  line
  line `(j) in the case of transfer of security through a depository, by the transferor of such security;`
  line
  line `(k) in the case of transfer of security otherwise than through a stock exchange or depository, by the`
  line `transferor of such security;`
  line
  line `(l) in the case of issue of security, whether through a stock exchange or a depository or otherwise, by`
  line `the issuer of such security; and`
  line
  line `(m) in the case of any other instrument not specified herein, by the person making, drawing or`
  line `executing such instrument.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Uttarakhand.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 29.--In Section 29 of the Principal Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) In clause (a), after the words (and figures, "No. 40 (Mortgage deed))," the words (and figures`
  line `"No. 43 (Note or memorandum))," shall be inserted;`
  line
  line `(b) after clause (f), the following clause shall be inserte`
  line `d, namely,--`
  line
  line `"'(f-f) in the case of an Instrument of Gift by the donee;"`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 1 of 2016, s. 4]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1904, s. 5, for ,"No. 6 (Agreement to Mortgage),".`
  line
  line `2. The words, figures and brackets ,"No. 27 (Debenture)," omitted by Act 7 of 2019, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2020). ic950Earlier notified w.e.f. 9-`
  line `1-2020 followed by 1-4-2020]`
  line
  line `3. The words, figures, brackets and letter ,"No. 62 (a) (Transfer of shares in an incorporated Company or other body corporate),"`
  line `omitted by s. 17, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2020). [Earlier notified w.e.f. 9-1-2020 followed by 1-4-2020]`
  line
  line `4. The words, figures, brackets and letter ,"No. 62 (b). (Transfer of debentures, being marketable securities, whether the debenture`
  line `is liable to duty or not, except debentures provided for by section 8),," omitted by s. 17,ibid (w.e.f. 1-4-2020). [Earlier notified`
  line `w.e.f. 9-1-2020 followed by 1-4-2020]`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 5 of 1906, s. 4, for clause (b).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-2020). [Earlier notified w.e.f. 9-1-2020 followed by 1-4-2020]`
  line
  line `7. The ,"and," omitted by s. 17, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2020). [Earlier notified w.e.f. 9-1-2020 followed by 1-4-2020]`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by s. 17, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2020). [Earlier notified w.e.f. 9-1-2020 followed by 1-4-2020]`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (45514)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 41
  title `Obligation to give receipt in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1. Added by Act 5 of 1906, s. 5.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45514&sectionno=30&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Any person receiving any money exceeding`
  line `twenty rupees in amount, or any bill of exchange, cheque or promissory note for an amount exceeding`
  line `twenty rupees, or receiving in satisfaction or part satisfaction of a debt any moveable property exceeding`
  line `twenty rupees in value, shall, on demand by the person paying or delivering such money, bill, cheque,`
  line `note or property, give a duly stamped receipt for the same.`
  line
  line `^1[Any person receiving or taking credit for any premium or consideration for any renewal of any`
  line `contract of fire-insurance, shall, within one month after receiving or taking credit for such premium or`
  line `consideration, give a duly stamped receipt for the same. ]`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (45515)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 42
  title `Adjudication as to proper stamp.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1958, s. 3, for "eight annas" (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45515&sectionno=31&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any instrument, whether executed or not and`
  line `whether previously stamped or not, is brought to the Collector, and the person bringing it applies to have`
  line `the opinion of that officer as to the duty (if any) with which it is chargeable, and pays a fee of such`
  line `amount (not exceeding five rupees and not less than ^1[fifty naye paise]) as the Collector may in each case`
  line `direct, the Collector shall determine the duty (if any) with which, in his judgment, the instrument is`
  line chargeable.
  line
  line `(2) For this purpose the Collector may require to be furnished with an abstract of the instrument, and`
  line `also with such affidavit or other evidence as he may deem necessary to prove that all the facts and`
  line `circumstances affecting the chargeability of the instrument with duty, or the amount of the duty with`
  line `which it is chargeable, are fully and truly set forth therein, and may refuse to proceed upon any such`
  line `application until such abstract and evidence have been furnished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) no evidence furnished in pursuance of this section shall be used against any person in any`
  line `civil proceeding, except in an inquiry as to the duty with which the instrument to which it relates is`
  line `chargeable; and`
  line
  line `(b) every person by whom any such evidence is furnished, shall, on payment of the full duty with`
  line `which the instrument to which it relates, is chargeable, be relieved from any penalty which he may`
  line `have incurred under this Act by reason of the omission to state truly in such instrument any of the`
  line `facts or circumstances aforesaid.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 31.--In section 31 of the principal Act, in sub-section (1), for the words "not`
  line `exceeding five rupees" and "not less than fifty naye paise", the words "not exceeding twenty rupees" and`
  line `"not less than five rupees", shall respectively be substituted..`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 1 of 2003, s. 4]`
  line
  line Uttarakhand.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 31.----In sub-section (1), for the words, "Pays a fee of such amount not`
  line `exceeding five rupees and not less than fifty paisa as the collector may in Each case direct," the words,`
  line `"Pays a fee such amount as may be fixed by State Government By notification in the Official Gazette",`
  line `shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 1 of 2016, s. 5]`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (45516)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 43
  title `Certificate by Collector.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45516&sectionno=32&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) When an instrument brought to the Collector under section 31 is,`
  line `in his opinion, one of a description chargeable with duty, and`
  line
  line `(a) the Collector determines that it is already fully stamped, or`
  line
  line `(b) the duty determined by the Collector under section 31, or such a sum as, with the duty already`
  line `paid in respect of the instrument, is equal to the duty so determined, has been paid,`
  line
  line `the Collector shall certify by endorsement on such instrument that the full duty (stating the amount) with`
  line `which it is chargeable has been paid.`
  line
  line `(2) When such instrument is, in his opinion, not chargeable with duty, the Collector shall certify in`
  line `manner aforesaid that such instrument is not so chargeable.`
  line
  line `(3) Any instrument upon which an endorsement has been made under this section, shall be deemed to`
  line `be duly stamped or not chargeable with duty, as the case may be; and, if chargeable with duty, shall be`
  line `receivable in evidence or otherwise, and may be acted upon and registered as if it had been originally duly`
  line `stamped:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall authorize the Collector to endorse--`
  line
  line `(a) any instrument executed or first executed in ^1[India] and brought to him after the expiration of`
  line `one month from the date of its execution or first execution, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) any instrument executed or first executed out of ^1[India] and brought to him after the`
  line `expiration of three months after it has been first received in ^1[India]; or`
  line
  line `(c) any instrument chargeable ^2[with a duty not exceeding ten naye paise], or any bill of exchange`
  line `or promissory note, when brought to him, after the drawing or execution thereof, on paper not duly`
  line stamped.
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Himachal Pradesh.`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 32.-- In section 32 of the said Act.--`
  line
  line `(1) in clause (a) of the proviso, after the words "any instrumentsbqts the words "other than an instrument chargeable with a duty under clause (bb) of the first proviso to section 3 as amended by the Indian Stamp (Himachal Pradesh Amendment) Act, 1952" shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `(2) the word "or" at the end of clause (b) of the proviso shall be omitted,`
  line
  line `(3) after clause (c) of the proviso the word "or" shall be inserted, and the following new clause shall be added:--`
  line
  line `(d) any instrument chargeable with duty under clause (bb) of the first proviso to section 3 as amended by the Indian Stamp (Himachal Pradesh Amendment) Act, 1952, and brought to him after the expiration of three months from the date on which it is first received in Himachal Pradesh.`
  line
  line `[Vide Himachal Pradesh Act 4 of 1953, s. 10]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 1955 s. 2 for "the States" (w.e.f. 1-4-1956).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 19 of 1958, s. 4 for "with the Duty of one anna or half an anna" (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (45517)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 44
  title `Examination and impounding of instruments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45517&sectionno=33&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person having by law or consent of`
  line `parties authority to receive evidence, and every person in charge of a pubic office, except an officer of`
  line `police, before whom any instrument, chargeable, in his opinion, with duty, is produced or comes in the`
  line `performance of his functions, shall, if it appears to him that such instrument is not duly stamped, impound`
  line `the same.`
  line
  line `(2) For that purpose every such person shall examine every instrument so chargeable and so produced`
  line `or coming before him, in order to ascertain whether it is stamped with a stamp of the value and`
  line `description required by the law in force in ^1[India] when such instrument was executed or first executed:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) nothing herein contained shall be deemed to require any Magistrate or Judge of a Criminal`
  line `Court to examine or impound, if he does not think fit so to do, any instrument coming before him in`
  line `the course of any proceeding other than a proceeding under Chapter XII or Chapter XXXVI of the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (V of 1898);`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a Judge of a High Court, the duty of examining and impounding any instrument`
  line `under this section may be delegated to such officer as the Court appoints in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this section, in cases of doubt,--`
  line
  line `(a)`
  line `^2[the ^3[State Government]] may determine what offices shall be deemed to be public offices;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b)`
  line `^4[the ^2[State Government]] may determine who shall be deemed to be persons in charge of`
  line `public offices.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 33.--In section 33 of the principal Act after sub-section (1), the`
  line `following sub-sections shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(1-a) If it appears to such person from the copy of an instrument produced or coming in performance`
  line `of his functions, within three years from the date of registration of the instrument, that such instrument is`
  line `not duly stamped, he shall call for the original instrument and if he is satisfied on production of the`
  line `instrument that it has not been duly stamped, impound the same and the deficient amount of duty shall be`
  line `payable by the person liable to pay the duty.`
  line
  line `"(1-b) Where the original instrument is not produced such person shall refer the copy of the instrument`
  line `to the Collector for determination of the market value of the property and the duty payable thereon and`
  line `the Collector may determine the market value of the property and the duty as aforesaid in accordance with`
  line `the procedure provided for in sub-section (2) of section 47-A.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 7 of 1987, s. 5]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 33 of Act no. 11 of 1899.—In section 33 of the Indian Stamp Act, 1899, as`
  line `amended in its application to Uttar Pradesh, hereinafter in this Chapter referred to as the principal Act, --`
  line
  line `(i) in sub-section (2), in the proviso, in clause (a), for the words and figures`
  line `Chapter XII or Chapter XXXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898”, the words and figures`
  line `“sections 125 to 128 and sections 145 to 148 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973” shall be`
  line substituted.
  line
  line `(ii) after sub-section (2), for the existing sub-sections, the following sub-sections shall be`
  line `substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `“(3) For the purpose of this section the State Government may in cases of doubt, determine`
  line `what offices shall be deemed to be public offices and who shall be deemed to be persons in`
  line `charge of public offices.`
  line
  line `(4) Where deficiency in stamp duty paid is noticed from the any court or from the`
  line `Commissioner of Stamps or an, Additional Commissioner of Stamp or a Deputy Commissioner`
  line `of Stamps or an Assistant Commissioner of Stamps or any officer authorized by the Board of`
  line `Revenue in that behalf, call for the original instrument so purpose, and the instrument so`
  line `produced before the Collector shall be deemed to have been produced or come before him in the`
  line `performance of his functions.`
  line
  line `(5) In case the instrument is not produced within the period specified by the Collector, he`
  line `may require payment of deficit stamp duty, if any, together with penalty under section 40 on the`
  line `copy of the instrument:`
  line
  line `Provided that no action under sub-section (4) or sub-section (5) shall be taken after a period`
  line `of four years from the date of execution of the instrument.”`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 6 of 1980, s. 6]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 1955, s. 2, for "the States" (w.e.f. 1-4-1956).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "the G.G. in C.".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "collecting Government".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "the L.G.".`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (45518)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 45
  title `Special provision as to unstamped receipts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1958, s. 5, for "with a duty of one anna" (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45518&sectionno=34&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Where any receipt chargeable ^1[with a duty not`
  line `exceeding ten naye paise] is tendered to or produced before any officer unstamped in the course of the`
  line `audit of any public account, such officer may in his discretion, instead of impounding the instrument,`
  line `require a duly stamped receipt to be substituted therefore.`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (45519)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 46
  title `Instruments not duly stamped inadmissible in evidence, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 69, for not being an instrument chargeable with a duty not exceeding ten naye paise only, or a bill of exchange or promissory note, shall, subject to all just exceptions,`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45519&sectionno=35&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `No instrument chargeable`
  line `with duty shall be admitted in evidence for any purpose by any person having by law or consent of parties`
  line `authority to receive evidence, or shall be acted upon, registered or authenticated by any such person or by`
  line `any public officer, unless such instrument is duly stamped :`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) any such instrument ^1[shall] be admitted in evidence on payment of the duty with which the`
  line `same is chargeable, or, in the case of any instrument insufficiently stamped, of the amount required to`
  line `make up such duty, together with a penalty of five rupees, or, when ten times the amount of the`
  line `proper duty or deficient portion thereof exceeds five rupees, of a sum equal to ten times such duty or`
  line portion;
  line
  line `(b) where any person from whom a stamped receipt could have been demanded, has given an`
  line `unstamped receipt and such receipt, if stamped, would be admissible in evidence against him, then`
  line `such receipt shall be admitted in evidence against him on payment of a penalty of one rupee by the`
  line `person tendering it;`
  line
  line `(c) where a contract or agreement of any kind is effected by correspondence consisting of two or`
  line `more letters and any one of the letters bears the proper stamp, the contract or agreement shall be`
  line `deemed to be duly stamped;`
  line
  line `(d) nothing herein contained shall prevent the admission of any instrument in evidence in any`
  line `proceeding in a Criminal Court, other than a proceeding under Chapter XII or Chapter XXXVI of the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure 1898 (V of 1898);`
  line
  line `(e) nothing herein contained shall prevent the admission of any instrument in any Court when`
  line `such instrument has been executed by or on behalf of the Government, or where it bears the`
  line `certificate of the Collector as provided by section 32 or any other provision of this Act.`
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 35.--In section 35 of the principal Act, in the proviso in clause (d), for the`
  line `words and figures Chapter XII or Chapter XXXVI of the Code of criminal Procedure, 1898, the words`
  line `and figures sections 125 to 128 and sections 145 to 148 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 shall`
  line `be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 6 of 1980, s. 7]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 35. In section 35 of the principal Act, in clause (a) of the proviso for the`
  line `words five rupees. or, when ten times the amount of the proper duty of deficient portion thereof exceeds`
  line `five rupees, of a sum equal to ten times such duty or portion: the following words shall be substituted,`
  line `namely :--`
  line
  line `a sum equal to ten times the amount of the proper duty or deficient portion thereof ;`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 22 of 1998, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (45520)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 47
  title `Admission of instrument where not to be questioned.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45520&sectionno=36&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Where an instrument has been`
  line `admitted in evidence, such admission shall not, except as provided in section 61, be called in question at`
  line `any stage of the same suit or proceeding on the ground that the instrument has not been duly stamped.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (45521)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 48
  title `Admission of improperly stamped instruments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45521&sectionno=37&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `^1[The ^2[State Government]] may make rules`
  line `providing that, where an instrument bears a stamp of sufficient amount but of improper description, it`
  line `may, on payment of the duty with which the same is chargeable, be certified to be duly stamped, and any`
  line `instrument so certified shall then be deemed to have been duly stamped as from the date of its execution.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "the G.G. in C"..`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A. O. 1950, for "collecting Government".`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (45522)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 49
  title `Instruments impounded how dealt with.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45522&sectionno=38&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the person impounding an instrument`
  line `under section 33 has by law or consent of parties authority to receive evidence and admits such`
  line `instrument in evidence upon payment of a penalty as provided by section 35 or of duty as provided by`
  line `section 37, he shall send to the Collector an authenticated copy of such instrument, together with a`
  line `certificate in writing, stating the amount of duty and penalty levied in respect thereof, and shall send such`
  line `amount to the Collector, or to such person as he may appoint in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) In every other case, the person so impounding an instrument shall send it in original to the`
  line Collector.
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (45523)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 50
  title `Collector's power to refund penalty paid under section 38, sub-section (1).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45523&sectionno=39&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a`
  line `copy of an instrument is sent to the Collector under section 38, sub-section (1), he may, if he thinks fit,`
  line `^1*** refund any portion of the penalty in excess of five rupees which has been paid in respect of such`
  line instrument.
  line
  line `(2) When such instrument has been impounded only because it has been written in contravention of`
  line `section 13 or section 14, the Collector may refund the whole penalty so paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "upon application made to him in this behalf or, if no application is made, with the consent of the chief`
  line `Controlling Revenue-authority" omitted by Act 4 of 1914, s. 2 and the Sch. Pt I.`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (45524)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 51
  title `Collector's power to stamp instruments impounded.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45524&sectionno=40&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the Collector impounds any`
  line `instrument under section 33, or receives any instrument sent to him under section 38, sub-section (2), not`
  line `being an instrument chargeable ^1[with a duty not exceeding ten naye paise] only or a bill of exchange or promissory note, he shall adopt the following procedure:--`
  line
  line `(a) if he is of opinion that such instrument is duly stamped, or is not chargeable with duty, he shall certify by endorsement thereon that it is duly stamp, or that it is not so chargeable, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) if he is of opinion that such instrument is chargeable with duty and is not duly stamped, he shall require the payment of the proper duty or the amount required to make up the same, together with a penalty of five rupees; or, if he thinks fit, ^2[an amount not exceeding] ten times the amount of the proper duty or of the deficient portion thereof, whether such amount exceeds or falls short of five`
  line `rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that, when such instrument has been impounded only because it has been written in`
  line `contravention of section 13 or section 14, the Collector may, if he thinks fit, remit the whole penalty`
  line `prescribed by this section.`
  line
  line `(2) Every certificate under clause (a) of sub-section (1) shall, for the purposes of this Act, be`
  line `conclusive evidence of the matters stated therein.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an instrument has been sent to the Collector under section 38, sub-section (2), the Collector shall, when he has dealt with it as provided by this section, return it to the impounding officer.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Uttarakhand.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 40.--After sub-section (1), the following sub-sections shall be inserted,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `"(1-A) The Collector shall also require, alongwith the amount of deficit Stamp Duty of penalty`
  line `required to be paid under clause (b) of sub-section (1), the payment of a simple interest at the rate of one`
  line `and half percent per mensem on the amount of deficit stamp duty calculated from the date of the`
  line `execution of the instrument till the date of actual payment;`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount of interest under this sub-section shall be recalculated if the amount of`
  line `deficit stamp duty is varied on appeal or revision or by any order of a competent court or authority.`
  line
  line `(1-B) The amount of interest payable under sub-section (1-A) shall be added to the amount due and`
  line `be also deemed for all purposes to part of the amount required to be paid.`
  line
  line `(1-C) Where realization of the deficit stamp duty reminded stayed by any order of any court or`
  line `authority and such order of stay is subsequently vacated, the interest referred to in sub-section (1-A) shall`
  line `be payable also for any period during which such order of stay remain in operation.`
  line
  line `(1-D) Any amount paid or deposited by, or removed, or refundable to a person under the provisions`
  line `of this Act, shall first be adjusted towards the deficit stamp duty or penalty outstanding against him and`
  line `the excess, if any, shall then be adjusted towards the interest, in any, due from him."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 1 of 2016, s. 6]`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1958, s. 6, for "with a duty of one anna or half an anna" (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 15 of 1904, s. 6.`
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (45525)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 52
  title `Instruments unduly stamped by accident.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1958, s. 6 for "with a duty of one anna or half an anna" (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45525&sectionno=41&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `If any instrument chargeable with duty and not`
  line `duly stamped, not being an instrument chargeable ^1[with a duty not exceeding ten naye paise] only or a`
  line `bill of exchange or promissory note, is produced by any person of his own motion before the Collector`
  line `within one year from the date of its execution or first execution, and such person brings to the notice of`
  line `the Collector the fact that such instrument is not duly stamped and offers to pay to the Collector the`
  line `amount of the proper duty, or the amount required to make up the same, and the Collector is satisfied that`
  line `the omission to duly stamp such instrument has been occasioned by accident, mistake or urgent necessity,`
  line `he may, instead of proceeding under sections 33 and 40, receive such amount and proceed as next herein`
  line `after prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (45526)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 53
  title `Endorsement of instruments on which duty has been paid under sections 35, 40 or 41.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), Sch. I, Order XIII, Rule 9.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45526&sectionno=42&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `When the duty and penalty (if any), leviable in respect of any instrument have been paid under section 35,`
  line `section 40 or section 41, the person admitting such instrument in evidence or the Collector, as the case`
  line `may be, shall certify by endorsement thereon that the proper duty or, as the case may be, the proper duty`
  line `and penalty (stating the amount of each) have been levied in respect thereof, and the name and residence`
  line `of the person paying them.`
  line
  line `(2) Every instrument so endorsed shall thereupon be admissible in evidence, and may be registered`
  line `and acted upon and authenticated as if it had been duly stamped, and shall be delivered on his application`
  line `in this behalf to the person from whose possession it came into the hands of the officer impounding it, or`
  line `as such person may direct:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) no instrument which has been admitted in evidence upon payment of duty and a penalty under`
  line `section 35, shall be so delivered before the expiration of one month from the date of such`
  line `impounding, or if the Collector has certified that its further detention is necessary and has not`
  line `cancelled such certificate;`
  line
  line `(b) nothing in this section shall affect the^1 Code of Civil Procedure (XIV of 1882), section 144,clause 3.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Uttarakhand.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 42.--In section 42 of the Principal Act, --`
  line
  line `(a) in the heading, of the words and figures "Sections 35, 40 or 41", the words and figures,`
  line `"sections 35, 40, 41 or 47-A" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (1), for the words and figures "section 40 or section 41", the words and figures,`
  line `"section 40, section 41 or section 47-A" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 1 of 2016, s. 7]`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (45527)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 54
  title `Prosecution for offence against Stamp-law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45527&sectionno=43&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `The taking of proceedings or the payment of a`
  line `penalty under this Chapter in respect of any instrument shall not bar the prosecution of any person who`
  line `appears to have committed an offence against the Stamp-law in respect of such instrument:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such prosecution shall be instituted in the case of any instrument in respect of which`
  line `such a penalty has been paid, unless it appears to the Collector that the offence was committed with an`
  line `intention of evading payment of the proper duty.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (45528)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 55
  title `Persons paying duty or penalty may recover same in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45528&sectionno=44&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any duty or`
  line `penalty has been paid under section 35, section 37, section 40 or section 41, by any person in respect of`
  line `an instrument, and, by agreement or under the provisions of section 29 or any other enactment in force at`
  line `the time such instrument was executed, some other person was bound to bear the expense of providing the`
  line `proper stamp for such instrument, the first-mentioned person shall be entitled to recover from such other`
  line `person the amount of the duty or penalty so paid.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of such recovery, any certificate granted in respect of such instrument under this Act shall be conclusive evidence of the matters therein certified.`
  line
  line `(3) Such amount may, if the Court thinks fit, be included in any order as to costs in any suit or`
  line `proceeding to which such persons are parties and in which such instrument has been tendered in evidence.`
  line `If the Court does not include the amount in such order, no further proceedings for the recovery of the`
  line `amount shall be maintainable.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (45529)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 56
  title `Power to Revenue-authority to refund penalty or excess duty in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45529&sectionno=45&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where`
  line `any penalty is paid under section 35 or section 40, the Chief Controlling Revenue-authority may, upon`
  line `application in writing made within one year from the date of the payment, refund such penalty wholly or`
  line `in part.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, in the opinion of the Chief Controlling Revenue-authority, stamp-duty in excess of that`
  line `which is legally chargeable has been charged and paid under section 35 or section 40, such authority may,`
  line `upon application in writing made within three months of the order charging the same, refund the excess`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (45530)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 57
  title `Non-liability for loss of instruments sent under section 38.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45530&sectionno=46&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any instrument sent to the`
  line `Collector under section 38, sub-section (2), is lost, destroyed or damaged during transmission, the person`
  line `sending the same shall not be liable for such loss, destruction or damage.`
  line
  line `(2) When any instrument is about to be so sent, the person from whose possession it came into the`
  line `hands of the person impounding the same, may require a copy thereof to be made at the expense of such`
  line `first-mentioned person and authenticated by the person impounding such instrument`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (45531)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 58
  title `Power of payer to stamp bills, and promissory notes received by him unstamped.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45531&sectionno=47&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `When any bill of exchange ^1[or promissory note] chargeable ^2[with a duty not exceeding ten nayepaise] is`
  line `presented for payment unstamped, the person to whom it is so presented, may affix thereto the necessary`
  line `adhesive stamp, and, upon cancelling the same in manner hereinbefore provided, may pay the sum`
  line `payable upon such bill ^3[or note], and may charge the duty against the person who ought to have paid the`
  line `same, or deduct it from the sum payable as aforesaid, and such bill ^3[or note], shall, so far as respects the`
  line `duty, be deemed good and valid:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing herein contained shall relieve any person from any penalty or proceeding to`
  line `which he may be liable in relation to such bill, ^3[or note].`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Himachal Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Insertion of section 47-A. --After section 47 of the principal Act, the following new section shall be`
  line `added, namely:--`
  line
  line `47-A. Instruments under-valued, how to be dealt with.--(1) If the Registering Officer, appointed`
  line `under the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908) while registering any instrument relating to the transfer of`
  line `any property, has reason to believe that the market value of the property or the consideration, as the case`
  line `may be, has not been truly set forth in the instrument, he may, after registering such instrument, refer the`
  line `same to the Collector for determination of the market value or consideration, as the case may be, and the`
  line `proper duty payable thereon.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of reference under sub-section (1), the Collector shall, after giving the parties a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard and after holding an enquiry in such manner, as may be prescribed`
  line `by rules, made under this Act, determine the market value or consideration and the duty, as aforesaid, and`
  line `the deficient amount of duty, if any, shall be payable by the person liable to pay the duty.`
  line
  line `(3) The Collector may, suo moto or on receipt of reference from the Inspector General of Registration`
  line `or the Registrar of a District, in whose jurisdiction the property, or any portion thereof, which is the`
  line `subject-matter of the instrument, is situated, appointed under the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908)`
  line `shall, within three years from the date of registration of any instrument, not already referred to him under`
  line `sub-section (1), call for and examine the instrument for the purpose of satisfying himself as to the`
  line `correctness of its market value or consideration, as the case may be, and the duty payable thereon and if,`
  line `after such examination, he has reason to believe that the market value or consideration has not been truely set forth in the instrument, he may determine the market value or consideration and the duty, as aforesaid,`
  line `in accordance with procedure provided for in sub-section (2), and the deficient amount of duty, if any,`
  line `shall be payable by the person liable to pay the duty:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to any instrument registered before the date of the`
  line `commencement of the Indian Stamp (Himachal Pradesh Amendment) Act, 1988.`
  line
  line `(4) Where for any reason the original document called for by the Collector under sub-section (3) is not`
  line `produced or cannot be produced, the Collector may, after recording the reasons for its nonproduction, call`
  line `for a certified copy of the entries of the document from the registering officer concerned and exercise the`
  line `powers conferred on him under sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) Any person, aggrieved by an order of the Collector, under subsection (2) or sub-section (3), may,`
  line `within thirty days from the date of the order, prefer an appeal before the District Judge and all such`
  line `appeals shall be heard and disposed off in such manner as may be prescribed by rules made under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(6) For the purpose of this section "market value" of any property shall be estimated to be the price`
  line `which, in the opinion of the Collector or the appellate authority, as the case may be, such property would`
  line `have fetched, if sold in the open market on the date of execution of the instrument relating to the transfer`
  line `of such property.`
  line
  line `[Vide Himachal Pradesh Act 7 of 1989, s. 3]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 47-A, (Act 2 of 1899). In section 47-A of the Indian Stamp Act, 1899`
  line `(Act 2 of 1899)-`
  line
  line `(a) after sub-section (2), the following new sub-section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(2-a) The Collector may sou motu, within two years from the date of registration of any`
  line `instrument not already referred to him under sub-section (1), call for purpose of satisfying himself as`
  line `to the correctness of its value or consideration, as the case may be, and the duty payable thereon and if`
  line `after such examination, he has reasons to believe that the value or consideration has not been truly set`
  line `forth in the instrument, he may determine the value or consideration and the duty as aforesaid in`
  line `accordance with the procedure provided for in sub-section (2); and the deficient amount of duty, if`
  line `any, shall be payable by the person liable to pay the duty.";`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (3), after the word, brackets and figure "sub-section (2)" the words, brackets,`
  line `figure and letter "or sub-section (2-a)" shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 11 of 1965, s. 2]`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 47-A.--In section 47-A of the principal Act, in sub-section (2-a), for the`
  line `words "two years", the words "three years" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 1 of 2003, s. 5]`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `(a) Amendment of section 47-A.--for sub-section (1) the following sub-section shall be`
  line `substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `(1) where the registering officer under the Registration Act, 1908, (16 of 1908) while registering`
  line `any instrument of conveyance, exchange, gift, partition or settlement has reasons to believe that the`
  line `market value of the property which is the subject matter of such instrument has not been rightly set`
  line `forth in the instrument or is less than the minimum value determined in accordance with the rules`
  line `made under this Act, he shall, before registering such instrument, refer the matter to the Collector,`
  line `with an intimation in writing to the person concerned, for determination of the market value of such`
  line `property and the proper duty payable thereon.; and`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (2-a) for the words "truly set forth in the instrument" , the words "rightly set`
  line `forth in the instrument or is less than the minimum value determined in accordance with the rules`
  line `made under this Act" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 8 of 2009, s. 2]`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 47-A, Act 2 of 1899. --After section 47 of the Indian Stamp Act, 1899 (2 of`
  line `1899) (hereinafter referred to as the Principal Act), the following new section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `47-A. Instruments under-valued how to be dealt with -- (1) If the registering officer appointed under the Indian Registration Act, 1908, while registering any instrument transferring any property, has reasons to believe that the value of the property or the consideration, as the case may be, has not been truly set forth in the instrument, he may, after registering such instrument, refer the same to the Collector for determination of the value or consideration, as the case may be, and the proper duty payable thereon.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of a reference under sub-section (1) the Collector shall, after giving the parties a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard and after holding an enquiry in such manner as may be prescribed by rules made under this Act, determine the value or consideration and the duty as aforesaid and the deficient amount of duty, if any, shall be payable by the person liable to pay the duty.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person aggrieved by an order of the Collector under sub-section (2) may, within thirty days from the date of the order, prefer an appeal before the District judge and all such appeals shall be heard and disposed of in such manner as may be prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 35 of 1962, s. 2]`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 47-A.-- In section 47-A of the Principal Act, for sub-sections (1), (2) and`
  line `(2-a), the following sub-sections shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(1) Where the registering officer under the Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), while registering any`
  line `instrument of conveyance, exchange, gift, partition or settlement has reason to believe that the market`
  line `value of the property which is the subject matter of such instrument has not been truly set forth in the`
  line `instrument, he may, after registering such instrument, refer the matter to the Collector for determination`
  line `of the market value of such property and the proper duty payable thereon.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of a reference under sub-section (1), the Collector shall, after giving the parties an`
  line `opportunity of making their representations and after holding an enquiry in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by rules made under this Act, determine the market value of the property which is the subject`
  line `matter of such instrument, and the duty as aforesaid and the deficient amount, if any, shall be payable by`
  line `the person liable to pay the duty.`
  line
  line `(2-a) The Collector may suo motu within two years from the date of registration of such instrument,`
  line `not already referred to him under sub-section (1), call for and examine the instrument for the purpose of`
  line `satisfying himself as to the correctness of the market value of the property which is the subject matter of`
  line `such instrument and the duty payable thereon and if after such examination, he has reason to believe that`
  line `the market value of such property has not been truly set forth in the instrument, he may determine the`
  line `market value of such property and the duty as aforesaid in accordance with the procedure provided for in`
  line `sub-section (2) and the deficient amount of duty , if any, shall be payable by the person liable to pay the`
  line `duty".`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 7 of 1987, s. 6]`
  line
  line Tripura.--
  line
  line `In the Indian Stamp Act, 1899 as in force in the State of Tripura, after section 47, the following new`
  line `section shall be inserted namely: --`
  line
  line `"47A" Instruments of conveyance etc. undervalued, how to be, dealt with :--`
  line `(1) If the Registering Officer appointed under the Indian Registration Act, 1908 (Central Act XVI`
  line `of 1908), while registering any instrument of conveyance, exchange, gift or partition, has reason to`
  line `believe that the value of the property which is the subject matter of the instrument, as has been set`
  line `forth therein is lower than the market value thereof and proper duty has not been paid he may, after`
  line `registering such instrument, refer the same to the Collector for determination of the market value of`
  line `such property and the proper duty payable thereon.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of a reference under Sub-Section (1), the Collector shall, after giving the parties a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard and after holding an enquiry in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by rules made under this Act, determine the market value of such property and the proper`
  line `duty payable thereon and then return the instrument to the Registering Officer after making and`
  line `endorsement over his signature thereon indicating the market value of the property so determined and`
  line `deficient amount of duty, if any, that shall be payable by the person liable to pay the duty.`
  line
  line `(3) The Collector may, within a period of two year from the date of registration of any instrument`
  line `of conveyance, exchange, gift or partition, not already sent to him under sub-section (I), call for as`
  line `examine the instrument for the purpose of satisfying himself as to the correctness of the market value`
  line `of the property which is the subject matter of such instrument and the duty paid thereon and if after`
  line `such examination, he has reasons to believe that the market value of such property has not been truly`
  line `set forth in the instrument and the proper duty has not been truly set forth in the instrument and the`
  line `proper duty has not been paid, he may determine the market value thereof and the proper duty payable`
  line `thereon in accordance with the provision of sub-section (2). The difference, if any between the duty`
  line `determined by the Collector and the duty already paid shall be payable by the person liable to pay the`
  line `duty on the instrument:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to any instrument registered before the date of`
  line `the commencement of the Indian Stamp (Tripura Third Amendment) Act, 1984.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person aggrieved by an order of the Collector under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) may`
  line `appeal to the appellate authority specified in sub-section (5), All such appeals shall be preferred within`
  line `such time, and shall be heard and disposed of in such manner, as may be prescribed by rules made`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) The State Government shall, by a Notification in the Official Gazette, appoint a person not`
  line `below the rank of a Secretary of any Department to be the appellate authority referred to in`
  line `sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(6) The amount of deficient duty, if any, shall be paid by deposit into Government Treasury by the`
  line `person, liable to pay the duty, within a period of thirty days from the date of Notice in this behalf from the Registering Officer and in case of default in payment, such amount shall be recovered as arrears of`
  line `land revenue.`
  line
  line `Explanation:-- For the purpose of the section the market value of any property shall be estimated to`
  line `be the price which in the opinion of the Collector or the appellate authority, as the case may be, such`
  line `property would have fetched, if sold in the open market on the date of execution of the instrument of`
  line `conveyance, exchange gift or portion.`
  line
  line `[Vide Tripura Act 2 of 1986, s. 2]`
  line
  line Meghalaya.--
  line
  line `Insertion of new Section 47A in Act 11 of 1899.--In the Indian Stamp Act,1899 after the`
  line `existing Section 47, the following new Section as Section 47A, shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"47A. Instruments under-valued how to be dealt with.--(1) If registering officer`
  line `appointed under the Indian Registration Act, 1908, while registering any instrument transferring any`
  line `property, has reason to believe that the value of the property or the consideration, as the case may be`
  line `has not been truly set forth in the instrument, he may, after registering such instrument, refer the same`
  line `to the Deputy Commissioner, for determination of the value or consideration, as the case may be, and`
  line `the proper duty payable thereon.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of the reference under sub-section (1), the Deputy Commissioner shall, after giving`
  line `the parties a reasonable opportunity of being heard and after holding an enquiry in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed by rules made under this Act, by order, determine the value of the property or the`
  line `consideration and the duty aforesaid; and the deficient amount of duty, if any, shall be payable by the`
  line `person liable to pay the duty and, on payment of such duty, the Deputy Commissioner shall endorse a`
  line `certificate of such payment on the instrument under his seal and signature.`
  line
  line `(3) The Deputy Commissioner may, suo motu, within six months from the date of registration of`
  line `any instrument not already referred to him under sub-section (1), call for and examine the instrument`
  line `for the purpose of satisfying himself as to the correctness of its value or consideration, as the case`
  line `may be, and the duty payable thereon, and if after such examination, he has reason to believe that the`
  line `value of consideration has not been truly set forth in the instrument, she may determine the value or`
  line `consideration and the duty aforesaid in accordance with procedure provided for in sub-section (2);`
  line `and the deficient amount of duty if any, shall be payable by the person liable to pay the duty and, on`
  line `the payment of such duty the Deputy Commissioner shall endorse a certificate of such payment on the`
  line `instrument under his seal and signature.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person aggrieved by an order of the Deputy Commissioner under sub-section (2) or subsection (3) may appeal to the Meghalaya Board of Revenue.`
  line
  line `(5) An appeal under sub-section (4) shall be filed within 90 (ninety) days of the date of the order`
  line `sought to be appealed against."`
  line
  line `[Vide Meghalaya Act 8 of 1983, s. 2]`
  line
  line Uttarakhand.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 47-A.--In section 47-A of the Principal Act, :--`
  line
  line `(a) For sub-section (1), the following sub-sections shall be substituted, namely--`
  line
  line `"(1) (a) If the market value of any property which is the subject of any instrument, on which`
  line `duty is chargeable on the market value of the property as set forth in such instrument, is less than`
  line `even the minimum value determined in accordance with the rules made under this Act, the registering`
  line `officer appointed under the Registration Act, 1908 shall, notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line 39
  line `said Act, immediately after presentation of such instrument and before accepting it for registration`
  line `and taking any action under section 52 of the said Act, require the person liable to pay stamp duty`
  line `under section 29, to pay the deficit stamp duty as computed on the basis of the minimum value`
  line `determined in accordance with the said rules and return the instruments for presenting again in`
  line `accordance with section 23 of the Registration Act, 1908;`
  line
  line `(b) When the deficit stamp duty required to be paid under clause (a), is paid in respect of any`
  line `instrument and the instrument is presented again for registration, the registering officer shall certify`
  line `by endorsement thereon, that the deficit stamp duty has been paid in respect thereof and the name and`
  line `the residence of the person paying them and register the same;`
  line
  line `(c) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provisions of this Act, the deficit stamp duty`
  line `may be paid under clause (a) in the form of impressed stamps containing such declaration as may be`
  line prescribed;
  line
  line `(d) If any person does not make the payment of the deficit stamp duty after receiving the order`
  line `referred to in clause (a) and presents the instrument again for registration, the registering officer shall,`
  line `before registering the instrument, refer the same to the Collector, for determination of the market`
  line `value of the property and the proper duty payable thereon.`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (3) of section 47-A the following explanation shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"Explanation--The payment of deficit stamp duty by any person under any order of registering`
  line `officer under sub-section (1) shall not prevent the Collector from initiating proceedings on any`
  line `instrument under sub section (3)."`
  line
  line `(c) after sub-section (4), the following sub-section shall be inserted namely:--`
  line
  line `"(4-A) The Collector shall also require along with the deficit stamp duty or penalty required to be`
  line `paid under clause (ii) of sub-section (4), the payment of a simple interest at the rate of one and a half`
  line `per cent per mensem on the amount of deficit stamp duty calculated from the date of the execution of`
  line `the instrument till the date of actual payment;`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount of interest under this sub-Section shall be recalculated if the amount of`
  line `deficit stamp duty is varied on appeal or revision or by any order of a competent court or authority.`
  line
  line `(4-B) The amount of interest payable under sub section (4-A) shall be added to the amount due`
  line `and be also deemed for all purposes to be part of the amount required to be paid.`
  line
  line `(4-C) Where realization of the deficit stamp duty remained stayed by any order of any court or`
  line `authority and such order of stay is subsequently vacated, the interest referred to in sub-section (4-A)`
  line `shall be payable also for any period during which such order of stay remained in operation.`
  line
  line `(4-D) Any amount paid or deposited by or recovered from, or refundable to, a person under the`
  line `provision of this Act, shall first be adjusted towards the deficit stamp duty or penalty outstanding`
  line `against him and the excess if any, shall then be adjusted towards the interest, if any, due from him."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 1 of 2016, s. 8]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 47.In section 47-A of the principal Act, in sub-section (4), for the words,`
  line `"Chief Inspector of Stamp, Uttar Pradesh or any officer of the Stamp Department of the Board of`
  line `Revenue", the words "Commissioner of Stamps or an Additional Commissioner of Stamps or a Deputy`
  line `Commissioner of Stamps or an Assistant Commissioner of Stamps or any officer authorized by the Board`
  line `of Revenue in that behalf" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 6 of 1980, s. 8]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 47-A.--In section 47-A of the principal Act--`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (1) for the words, of conveyance, exchange, gift, settlement, award or trust"`
  line `the words "on which duty is chargeable on the market value of the property" shall be substituted ;`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (2) for the words "of conveyance, exchange, gift, settlement, award or trust"`
  line `where they occur for the first time, the words "on which duty is chargeable on the market value of the`
  line `property" and for the said words where they occur for the second time, the words "of such`
  line `instrument" shall be substituted ;`
  line
  line `(c) in sub-section (3), for the words "of conveyance, exchange, gift, settlement, award or trust,"`
  line `the words "of the instrument" shall be substituted ;`
  line
  line `(d) in sub-section (4) for the words, "of conveyance, exchange, gift, settlement, award or trust,"`
  line `where they occur for the first time, the words "on which duty is chargeable on the market value of the`
  line `property" and for the said words, where they occur for the second time, the words "of such`
  line `instrument" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 11 of 1992, s. 4]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 47-A.In section 47-A, in sub-section (4), for the words "two years", the`
  line `words "four- years" shall be substituted and be deemed always to have been substituted :`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 20 of 1974, s. 5]`
  line
  line `Substitution of section 47-AFor section 47-A of the principal Act. the following section shall be`
  line `substituted, namely :`
  line
  line `"47-A (1) If the market value of any property which is the subject of any instrument, on which`
  line `duty is chargeable on market value of such property, as set forth in such instrument, is less than even`
  line `the minimum value determined in accordance with the rules made under this Act, the registering`
  line `officer appointed under the Registration Act, 1908 shall, before registering the instrument, refer the`
  line `same to the Collector for determination of the market value of such property and the proper duty`
  line `payable thereon.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of a reference under sub-section (1) the Collector shall, after giving the parties`
  line `a reasonable opportunity of being heard and after holding an inquiry in such manner as many be`
  line `prescribed by rules made under this Act, determine the market value of the property which is the`
  line `subject of such instrument and the proper duty payable thereon.`
  line
  line `(3) The Collector may, suo motu, or on a reference from any court or from the Commissioner`
  line `of Stamps or an Additional Commissioner of Stamps or a Deputy Commissioner of Stamps or an`
  line `Assistant Commissioner of Stamps or any officer authorized by the State Government in that`
  line `behalf, within four years from the date of registration of any instrument on which duty is`
  line `chargeable on the market value of the property not already referred to him under sub-section (1)`
  line `call for and examine the instrument for the purpose of satisfying himself as to the correctness of`
  line `the market value of the property which is the subject for of such instrument, and the duty payable`
  line `thereon and if after such examination he has reason to believe that market value of such property`
  line `has not been truly set forth in such instrument he may determine the market value of such`
  line `property and the duty payable thereon :`
  line
  line `Provided that, with the prior permission of the State Government, an action under this sub-section`
  line `may be taken after a period of four years but before a period of eight years from the date of`
  line `registration of the instrument on which duty is chargeable on the market value of the properly.`
  line
  line `(4) If on enquiry under sub-section (2) and examination under sub-section (3) the Collector finds`
  line `the market value of the property :`
  line
  line `(i) truly set forth and the instrument duly Stamped, he shall certify by endorsement that it is`
  line `duly stamped and return it to the person who made the reference ;`
  line
  line `(ii) not truly set forth and the instrument not duly stamped he shall require the payment of`
  line `proper duty or the amount required to make up the deficiency in the same together with a penalty`
  line `of an amount not exceeding four time the amount of the proper duty or the deficient portion`
  line thereof.
  line
  line `(5) The instrument produced before the Collector under sub-section (2) or under sub-section (3)`
  line `shall be deemed to have come before him in the performance of his functions.`
  line
  line `(6) In case the instrument is not produced within the period specified by the Collector, he may`
  line `require payment of deficit stamp duty, if any, together with penalty on the copy of the instrument in`
  line `accordance with the procedure laid down in sub-sections (2) and (4).`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 22 of 1998, s. 6]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 47-A. in section 47-A of the principal Act,`
  line
  line `(a) for sub-section (1), the following sub-section shall be substituted, namely:`
  line
  line `"(1) (a) If the market value of any property which is the subject of any instrument, on which duty`
  line `is chargeable on the market value of the property as set forth in such instrument, is less than even the`
  line `minimum value determined in accordance with the rules made under this Act, the registering officer`
  line `appointed under the Registration Act, 1908 shall, notwithstanding anything contained in the said Act,`
  line `immediately after presentation of such instrument and before accepting it for registration and taking`
  line `any action under section 52 of the said Act, require the person liable to pay stamp duty under section`
  line `29, to pay the deficit stamp duty as computed on the basis of the minimum value determined in`
  line `accordance with the said rules and return the instrument for presenting again in accordance with`
  line `section 23 of the Registration Act, 1908.`
  line
  line `(b) When the deficit stamp duty required to be paid under clause (a), is paid in respect of any`
  line `instrument and the instrument is presented again for registration, the registering officer shall certify`
  line `by endorsement thereon, that the deficit stamp duty has been paid in respect thereof and the name and`
  line `the residence of the person paying them and register the same.`
  line
  line `(c) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provisions of this Act, the deficit stamp duty`
  line `may be paid under clause (a) in the form of impressed stamps containing such declaration as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(d) If any person does not make the payment of deficit stamp duty after receiving the order`
  line `referred to in clause (a) and presents the instrument again for registration, the registering officer shall,`
  line `before registering the instrument, refer the same to the Collector, for determination of the market value of`
  line `the property and the proper duty payable thereon."`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (3), the following explanation shall be inserted, namely :`
  line
  line `Explanation : The payment of deficit stamp duty by any person under any order of registering`
  line `officer under sub-section (1) shall not prevent the Collector from initiating proceedings on any`
  line `instrument under sub-section (3)."`
  line
  line `(c) after sub-section (4), the following sub-sections shall be inserted, namely :`
  line
  line `(4-A) The Collector shall also require along with the deficit stamp duty or penalty required to be`
  line `paid under clause (ii) of sub-section (4), the payment of a simple interest at the rate of one and half`
  line `per cent per mensem on the amount of deficit stamp duty calculated from the date of the execution of`
  line `the instrument till the date of actual payment :`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount of interest under this sub-section shall be recalculated if the amount of`
  line `deficit stamp duty is varied on appeal or revision or by any order of a competent court or authority.`
  line
  line `(4-B) The amount of interest payable under sub-section (4-A) shall be added to the amount due and be also deemed for all purposes to be part of the amount required to be paid.`
  line
  line `(4-C) Where realization of the deficit stamp duty remained stayed by any order of any court or`
  line `authority and such order of stay is subsequently vacated, the interest referred to in sub-section (4-A)`
  line `shall be payable also for any period during which such order of stay remained in operation.`
  line
  line `(4-D) Any amount paid or deposited by, or recovered from, or refundable to, a person under the`
  line `provision of this Act, shall first be adjusted towards the deficit stamp duty or penalty outstanding`
  line `against him and the excess, if any, shall then be adjusted towards the interest, if any, due front him."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 38 of 2001, s. 7]`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 47-A. In section 47-A of the principal, Act`
  line
  line `(a) in sub-section (1) for the words. "is less than that determined in accordance with any rules`
  line `made under this Act", the words, "is less than even the minimum value determined in accordance`
  line `with any rules made under this Act" shall be substituted ,`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (4), for the words, "or on a reference from Chief Inspector of Stamps, Uttar`
  line `Pradesh" the words, "or on a reference from any court or from the Chief Inspector of Stamps, Uttar`
  line `Pradesh or any officer of the Stamp Department of the Board of Revenue." shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 49 of 1975, s. 6]`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 1927, s. 5, for "promissory note or cheque".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 19 of 1958, s. 7, for "with the duty of one anna" (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 5 of 1927, s. 5, for "note or cheque".`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (45532)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 59
  title `Recovery of duties and penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45532&sectionno=48&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `All duties, penalties and other sums required to be paid`
  line `under this Chapter may be recovered by the Collector by distress and sale of the movable property of the`
  line `person from whom the same are due, or by any other process for the time being in force for the recovery`
  line `of arrears of land-revenue.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 48-A.--For Section 48-A of the Principal Act, the following section`
  line `shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"48-A. Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, no certificate or endorsement under this Act ,`
  line `in respect of any instrument chargeable in the State of Orissa with a higher rate of duty under this Act,`
  line `for the time being in force as amended from time to time by the Orissa Acts shall be received in`
  line `evidence or be in any way valid in respect of the payment of duty on such instrument or in respect of the`
  line `chargeability of such instrument with duty unless the duty chargeable under the Orissa Act, has been`
  line `paid on such instrument.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 7 of 1987, s. 7]`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (45533)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 60
  title `Allowance for spoiled stamps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45533&sectionno=49&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Subject to such rules as may be made by ^1[the ^2[State`
  line `Government ]] as to the evidence to be required, or the enquiry to be made, the Collector may, on`
  line `application made within the period prescribed in section 50, and if he is satisfied as to the facts, make`
  line `allowance for impressed stamps spoiled in the cases herein after mentioned, namely: --br`
  line
  line `(a) the stamp on any paper inadvertently and undesignedly spoiled, obliterated or by error in`
  line `writing or any other means rendered unfit for the purpose intended before any instrument written`
  line `thereon is executed by any person:`
  line
  line `(b) the stamp on any document which is written out wholly or in part, but which is not signed or`
  line `executed by any party thereto:`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of bills of exchange ^3[payable otherwise than on demand ] ^4*** or promissory`
  line notes--
  line
  line `(1) the stamp on ^5[any such bill of exchange] ^6***signed by or on behalf of the drawer which has`
  line `not been accepted or made use of in any manner whatever or delivered out of his hands for any`
  line `purpose other than by way of tender for acceptance: provided that the paper on which any such stamp`
  line `is impressed, does not bear any signature intended as or for the acceptance of any bill of`
  line `exchange ^6*** to be afterwards written thereon:`
  line
  line `(2) the stamp on any promissory note signed by or on behalf of the maker which has not been`
  line `made use of in any manner whatever or delivered out of his hands:`
  line
  line `(3) the stamp used or intended to be used for ^5[any such bill of exchange] ^7*** or promissory note`
  line `signed by, or on behalf of, the drawer thereof, but which from any omission or error has been spoiled`
  line `or rendered useless, although the same, being a bill of exchange ^6*** may have been presented for`
  line `acceptance or accepted or endorsed, or, being a promissory note, may have been delivered to the payee: provided that another completed and duly stamped bill of exchange ^7***or promissory note is`
  line `produced identical in every particular, except in the correction of such omission or error as aforesaid,`
  line `with the spoiled bill, ^7*** or note;`
  line
  line `(d) the stamp used for an instrument executed by any party thereto which--`
  line
  line `(1) has been afterwards found to be absolutely void in law from the beginning:`
  line
  line `(2) has been afterwards found unfit, by reason of any error or mistake therein, for the purpose`
  line `originally intended:`
  line
  line `(3) by reason of the death of any person by whom it is necessary that it should be executed,`
  line `without having executed the same, or of the refusal of any such person to execute the same, cannot be`
  line `completed so as to effect the intended transaction in the form proposed:`
  line
  line `(4) for want of the execution thereof by some material party, and his inability or refusal to sign`
  line `the same, is in fact incomplete and insufficient for the purpose for which it was intended:`
  line
  line `(5) by reason of the refusal of any person to act under the same, or to advance any money`
  line `intended to be thereby secured, or by the refusal or non-acceptance of any office thereby granted,`
  line `totally fails of the intended purpose:`
  line
  line `(6) becomes useless in consequence of the transaction intended to be thereby effected being`
  line `effected by some other instrument between the same parties and bearing a stamp of not less value:`
  line
  line `(7) is deficient in value and the transaction intended to be thereby effected has been effected by`
  line `some other instrument between the same parties and bearing a stamp of not less value:`
  line
  line `(8) is inadvertently and undesignedly spoiled, and in lieu whereof another instrument made`
  line `between the same parties and for the same purpose is executed and duly stamped:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in the case of an executed instrument, no legal proceeding has been commenced in`
  line `which the instrument could or would have been given or offered in evidence and that the instrument is`
  line `given up to be cancelled.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The certificate of the Collector under section 32 that the full duty with which an`
  line `instrument is chargeable, has been paid is an impressed stamp within the meaning of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for the L.G..`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "collecting Government".`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 5 of 1927, s. 5.`
  line
  line `4. The word "Cheques" omitted by s. 5, ibid.`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 5 of 1927, s. 5, for "any bill of exchange".`
  line
  line `6. The words or "cheque" omitted by s. 5, ibid.`
  line
  line `7. The word "cheque" omitted by s. 5, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (45534)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 61
  title `Application for relief under section 49 when to be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 43 of 1955, s. 2, for the States (w.e.f. 1-4-1956).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45534&sectionno=50&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `The application for relief under`
  line `section 49 shall be made within the following periods, that is to say,`
  line
  line `(1) in the cases mentioned in clause (d) (5), within two months of the date of the instrument:`
  line
  line `(2) in the case of a stamped paper on which no instrument has been executed by any of the parties`
  line `thereto, within six months after the stamp has been spoiled:`
  line
  line `(3) in the case of a stamped paper in which an instrument has been executed by any of the parties`
  line `thereto, within six months after the date of the instrument, or, if it is not dated, within six months after`
  line `the execution thereof by the person by whom it was first or alone executed:`
  line
  line `Provided that,`
  line
  line `(a) when the spoiled instrument has been for sufficient reasons sent out of ^1[India], the`
  line `application may be made within six months after it has been received back in ^1[India] ;`
  line
  line `(b) when, from unavoidable circumstances, any instrument for which another instrument has been`
  line `substituted, cannot be given up to be cancelled within the aforesaid period, the application may be`
  line `made within six months after the date of execution of the substituted instrument.`
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (45535)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 62
  title `Allowance in case of printed forms no longer required by Corporations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45535&sectionno=51&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `The Chief`
  line `Controlling Revenue-authority ^1[or the Collector if empowered by the Chief Controlling Revenueauthority in this behalf ] may, without limit of time, make allowance for stamped papers used for printed`
  line `forms of instruments ^2[by any banker] or by any incorporated company or other body corporate, if for any`
  line `sufficient reason such forms have ceased to be required by the said ^2[banker], company or body corporate:`
  line `provided that such authority is satisfied that the duty in respect of such stamped papers has been duly`
  line paid.
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1914, s. 2 and Sch. pt. 1.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 5 of 1906, s. 6.`
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (45536)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 63
  title `Allowance for misused stamps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45536&sectionno=52&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(a) When any person has inadvertently used for an instrument`
  line `chargeable with duty, a stamp of a description other than that prescribed for such instrument by the rules`
  line `made under this Act, or a stamp of greater value than was necessary, or has inadvertently used any stamp`
  line `for an instrument not chargeable with any duty; or`
  line
  line `(b) when any stamp used for an instrument has been inadvertently rendered useless under section 15,`
  line `owing to such instrument having been written in contravention of the provisions of section 13;`
  line
  line `the Collector may, on application made within six months after the date of the instrument, or, if it is`
  line `not dated, within six months after the execution thereof by the person by whom it was first or alone`
  line `executed, and upon the instrument, if chargeable with duty, being re-stamped with the proper duty, cancel`
  line `and allow as spoiled the stamp so misused or rendered useless.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (45537)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 64
  title `Allowance for spoiled or misused stamps how to be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1958, s. 8, for "one anna" (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45537&sectionno=53&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `In any case in which allowance`
  line `is made for spoiled or misused stamps, the Collector may give in lieu thereof--`
  line
  line `(a) other stamps of the same description and value; or`
  line
  line `(b) if required and he thinks fit, stamps of any other description to the same amount in value; or`
  line
  line `(c) at his discretion, the same value in money, deducting ^1[ten naye paise] for each rupee or fraction of a rupee.`
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (45538)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 65
  title `Allowance for stamps not required for use.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1958, s. 8, for "one anna" (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45538&sectionno=54&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `When any person is possessed of a stamp or`
  line `stamps which have not been spoiled or rendered unfit or useless for the purpose intended, but for which`
  line `he has no immediate use, the Collector shall repay to such person the value of such stamp or stamps in`
  line `money, deducting ^1[ten naye paise] for each rupee or portion of a rupee, upon such person delivering up`
  line `the same to be cancelled, and proving to the Collector's satisfaction--`
  line
  line `(a) that such stamp or stamps were purchased by such person with a bona fide intention to use`
  line `them; and`
  line
  line `(b) that he has paid the full price thereof; and`
  line
  line `(c) that they were so purchased within the period of six months next preceding the date on which`
  line `they were so delivered:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where the person is a licensed vendor of stamps, the Collector may, if he thinks fit,`
  line `make the repayment of the sum actually paid by the vendor without any such deduction as aforesaid.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_a:
  sectionId (45539)
  sectionNo 54A
  orderNo 66
  title `Allowances for stamps in denominations of annas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid.. (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45539&sectionno=54A&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_54_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[54A. Allowances for stamps in denominations of annas.-- Notwithstanding anything contained`
  line `in section 54, when any person is possessed of a stamp or stamps in any denominations, other than in`
  line `denominations of annas four of multiples thereof and such stamp or stamps has or have not been spoiled,`
  line `the Collector shall repay to such person the value of such stamp or stamps in money calculated in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 14 of the Indian Coinage`
  line `Act, 1906, (3 of 1906) upon such person delivering up, within six months from the commencement of the`
  line `Indian Stamp (Amendment) Act,1958 (19 of 1958), such stamp or stamps to the Collector.]`
obj_root_law_sections_54_b:
  sectionId (45540)
  sectionNo 54B
  orderNo 67
  title `Allowances for Refugee Relief stamps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 1973, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45540&sectionno=54B&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_54_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[54B. Allowances for Refugee Relief Stamps.-- Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 54, when any person is possessed of stamps bearing the inscription Refugee Relief (being`
  line `stamps issued in pursuance of section 3A before its omission) and such stamps have not been spoiled, the`
  line `Collector shall, upon such person delivering up, within six-month, from the commencement of the`
  line `Refugee Relief Taxes (Abolition) Act, 1973 (13 of 1973), such stamps to the Collector, refund to such`
  line `person the value of such stamps in money or give in lieu thereof other stamps of the same value:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may, with a view to facilitating expeditious disposal of claims for`
  line `such refunds, specify, in such manner as it deems fit, any other procedure which may also be followed for`
  line `claiming such refunds.]`
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (45541)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 68
  title `Allowance on renewal of certain debentures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A. O. 1937, for "the G.G. in C"..`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45541&sectionno=55&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `When any duly stamped debenture is renewed`
  line `by the issue of a new debenture in the same terms, the Collector shall, upon application made within one`
  line `month, repay to the person issuing such debenture, the value of the stamp on the original or on the new`
  line `debenture, whichever shall be less:`
  line
  line `Provided that the original debenture is produced before the Collector and cancelled by him in such`
  line `manner as ^1[the State Government] may direct.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- A debenture shall be deemed to be renewed in the same terms within the meaning of`
  line `this section notwithstanding the following changes:--`
  line
  line `(a) the issue of two or more debentures in place of one original debenture, the total amount`
  line `secured being the same;`
  line
  line `(b) the issue of one debenture in place of two or more original debentures, the total amount`
  line `secured being the same;`
  line
  line `(c) the substitution of the name of the holder at the time of renewal for the name of the original`
  line `holder; and`
  line
  line `(d) the alteration of the rate of interest or the dates of payment thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (45542)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 69
  title `Control of, and statement of case to, Chief Controlling Revenue-authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 1904, s. 7.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45542&sectionno=56&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `powers exercisable by a Collector under Chapter IV and Chapter V ^1[and under clause (a) of the first`
  line `proviso to section 26] shall in all cases be subject to the control of the Chief Controlling Revenueauthority.`
  line
  line `(2) If any Collector, acting under section 31, section 40 or section 41, feels doubt as to the amount of`
  line `duty with which any instrument is chargeable, he may draw up a statement of the case, and refer it, with`
  line `his own opinion thereon, for the decision of the Chief Controlling Revenue-authority.`
  line
  line `(3) Such authority shall consider the case and send a copy of its decision to the Collector, who shall`
  line `proceed to asses and charge the duty (if any) in conformity with such decision.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Uttarakhand.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 56.--In Section 56 of the Principal Act, after sub-section (1) the following`
  line `sub-section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(1-A) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provisions of this Act, any person Including`
  line `the Government aggrieved by any order of the Collector under chapter-IV, chapter-V or under clause (a)`
  line `of the first proviso to section 26 may, within 60 days from the date receipt of such order, prefer an appeal`
  line `against such order to the Chairman, Board of Revenue who shall, after giving the parties a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard consider the case and pass such order thereon as he thinks just and proper and`
  line `the order so passed shall be final.`
  line
  line `Provided that no application for stay of recovery of any disputed amount of stamp duty including`
  line `interest thereon or penalty shall be entertained unless the applicant has furnished satisfactory proof of the`
  line `payment of not less than one third of such disputed amount.`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the Chairman, Board of Revenue passes an order for the stay of recovery`
  line `of any stamp duty, interest thereon or penalty or for the stay of the operation of any order appealed`
  line `against and such order results in the stay of recovery of any stamp duty, interest thereon or penalty, such`
  line `stay order shall not remain in force for more than 30 days unless the appellant furnishes adequate security`
  line `to the satisfaction of the Collector concern for the payment of the outstanding amount."`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 1 of 2016, s. 9]`
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (45543)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 70
  title `Statement of case by Chief Controlling Revenue-authority to High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45543&sectionno=57&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief`
  line `Controlling Revenue-authority may state any case referred to it under section 56, sub-section (2), or`
  line `otherwise coming to its notice, and refer such case, with its own opinion thereon,--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) if it arises in a State, to the High Court for that State;`
  line
  line `^2[(b) if it arises in the Union territory of the Delhi, to the High Court of Delhi;]`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `^4[(c) if it arises in the Union territory of the Arunachal Pradesh or Mizoram, to the Gauhati High`
  line `Court (the High Court of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura;)]`
  line `(d) if it arises in the Union territory of the Andaman and Nicobar Islands, to the High Court at`
  line `Calcutta ;`
  line
  line `(e) if it arises in the Union territory of the ^5[Lakshadweep], to the High Court of Kerala;]`
  line
  line `^6[ (ee) if it arises in the Union territory of the Chandigarh, to the High Court of Punjab and Haryana;]`
  line
  line `^7[(f) if it arises in the Union territory of Dadra and Nagar Haveli, to the High Court of Bombay.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every such case shall be decided by not less than three Judges of the High Court ^8*** to which it`
  line `is referred, and in case of difference the opinion of the majority shall prevail.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. (No. 2) 1956, for clauses (a) to (g).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the Punjab Reorganisation and Delhi High Court (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1968,`
  line
  line `s. 3 and Sch. for clause (b) (w.e.f. 1-11-1966).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (bb) ins. by s. 3 and Sch. ibid. And omitted by the State of Himachal Pradesh (Adaptation of Law on Union Subjects) Order, 1973, s. 3 and Sch. (w.e.f. 25-1-1971).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order 1974, s. 3 and Sch. for clause (c) (w.e.f. 21-1-1972).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by the Laccadive, Minicoy and Amindivi Islands (Alteration of Name) Adaptation of Laws Order, 1974, s.`
  line `3 and Sch. for "the Laccadive, Minicoy and Amindivi Islands" (w.e.f. 1-11-1973).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by the Punjab Reorganisation and Delhi High Court (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1968, s. 3 and Sch. (w.e.f. 1-11-1966).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Reg. 6 of 1963, s. 2 and the First Sch.`
  line
  line `8. The words Chief Court or Judicial Commissioners Court omitted by the A.O. 1950.`
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (45544)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 71
  title `Power of High Court to call for further particulars as to case stated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes `1. The words Chief Court or Judicial Commissioners Court omitted by the A.O. 1948.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45544&sectionno=58&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `If the High Court`
  line `^1*** is not satisfied that the statements contained in the case are sufficient to enable it to determine the`
  line `questions raised thereby, the Court may refer the case back to the Revenue-authority by which it was`
  line `stated, to make such additions thereto or alterations therein as the Court may direct in that behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (45545)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 72
  title `Procedure in disposing of case stated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes `1. The words Chief Court or Judicial Commissioners Court omitted by the A.O. 1948.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45545&sectionno=59&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) The High Court, ^1*** upon the hearing of any such`
  line `case, shall decide the questions raised thereby, and shall deliver its judgment thereon containing the`
  line `grounds on which such decision is founded.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court shall send to the Revenue-authority by which the case was stated, a copy of such`
  line `judgment under the seal of the Court and the signature of the Registrar; and the Revenue-authority shall,`
  line `on receiving such copy, dispose of the case conformably to such judgment.`
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (45546)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 73
  title `Statement of case by other Courts to High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes `1. The words "Chief Court or Judicial Commissioner's Court" omitted by the A.O. 1948.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45546&sectionno=60&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any Court, other than a Court`
  line `mentioned in section 57, feels doubt as to the amount of duty to be paid in respect of any instrument`
  line `under proviso (a) to section 35, the Judge may draw up a statement of the case and refer it, with his own`
  line `opinion thereon, for the decision of the High Court ^1*** to which, if he were the Chief Controlling`
  line `Revenue-authority, he would, under section 57, refer the same.`
  line
  line `(2) Such Court shall deal with the case as if it had been referred under section 57, and send a copy of`
  line `its judgment under the seal of the Court and the signature of the Registrar to the Chief Controlling`
  line `Revenue-authority and another like copy to the Judge making the reference, who shall, on receiving such`
  line `copy, dispose of the case conformably to such judgment.`
  line
  line `(3) Reference made under sub-section (1), when made by a Court subordinate to a District Court,`
  line `shall be made through the District Court, and, when made by any subordinate Revenue Court, shall be`
  line `made through the Court immediately superior.`
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (45547)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 74
  title `Revision of certain decisions of Courts regarding the sufficiency of stamps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45547&sectionno=61&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any Court in the exercise of its civil or revenue jurisdiction or any Criminal Court in any proceeding under Chapter XII or Chapter XXXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (V of 1898), makes any order admitting any instrument in evidence as duly stamped or as not requiring a stamp, or upon payment of duty and a penalty under section 35, the Court to which appeals lie from, or references are made by, such first-mentioned Court may, of its own motion or on the application of the Collector, take such order into consideration.`
  line
  line `(2) If such Court, after such consideration, is of opinion that such instrument should not have been`
  line `admitted in evidence without the payment of duty and penalty under section 35, or without the payment`
  line `of a higher duty and penalty than those paid, it may record a declaration to that effect, and determine the`
  line `amount of duty with which such instrument is chargeable, and may require any person in whose`
  line `possession or power such instrument then is, to produce the same, and may impound the same when`
  line produced.
  line
  line `(3) When any declaration has been recorded under sub-section (2), the Court recording the same shall`
  line `send a copy thereof to the Collector, and, where the instrument to which it relates has been impounded or`
  line `is otherwise in the possession of such Court, shall also send him such instrument.`
  line
  line `(4) The Collector may thereupon, notwithstanding anything contained in the order admitting such`
  line `instrument in evidence, or in any certificate granted under section 42, or in section 43, prosecute any`
  line `person for any offence against the Stamp-law which the Collector considers him to have committed in`
  line `respect of such instrument:`
  line
  line `Provided that.--`
  line
  line `(a) no such prosecution shall be instituted where the amount (including duty and penalty) which,`
  line `according to the determination of such Court, was payable in respect of the instrument under`
  line `section 35, is paid to the Collector, unless he thinks that the offence was committed with an intention`
  line `of evading payment of the proper duty;`
  line
  line `(b) except for the purposes of such prosecution, no declaration made under this section shall`
  line `affect the validity of any order admitting any instrument in evidence, or of any certificate granted`
  line `under section 42.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 61. --In section 61 of the principal Act, in sub-section (1), for the words and`
  line `figures Chapter XII or Chapter XXXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898, the worth and figures sections 125 to 128 and sections 145 to 148 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 shall be`
  line substitute.
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 6 of 1980, s. 9]`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62_a:
  sectionId (49726)
  sectionNo 62A
  orderNo 75
  title `Penalty for failure to comply with provisions of section 9A.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=49726&sectionno=62A&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_62_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[62A. Penalty for failure to comply with provisions of section 9A.---(1) Any person who,--`
  line
  line `(a) being required under sub-section (1) of section 9A to collect duty, fails to collect the same; or`
  line
  line `(b) being required under sub-section (4) of section 9A to transfer the duty to the State`
  line `Government within fifteen days of the expiry of the time specified therein, fails to transfer within`
  line `such time,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with fine which shall not be less than one lakh rupees, but which may extend up to`
  line `one per cent. of the collection or transfer so defaulted.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who,--`
  line
  line `(a) being required under sub-section (5) of section 9A to submit details of transactions to the`
  line `Government, fails to submit the same; or`
  line
  line `(b) submits a document or makes a declaration which is false or which such person knows or`
  line `believes to be false,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with fine of one lakh rupees for each day during which such failure continues or one`
  line `crore rupees, whichever is less.]`
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (45548)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 76
  title `Penalty for executing, etc., instrument not duly stamped.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45548&sectionno=62&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person--`
  line
  line `(a) drawing, making, issuing, endorsing or transferring, or signing otherwise than as a witness, or`
  line `presenting for acceptance or payment, or accepting, paying or receiving payment of, or in any manner`
  line `negotiating, any bill of exchange ^1[payable otherwise than on demand] ^2*** or promissory note`
  line `without the same being duly stamped; or`
  line
  line `(b) executing or signing otherwise than as a witness any other instrument chargeable with duty without the same being duly stamped; or`
  line
  line `(c) voting or attempting to vote under any proxy not duly stamped;`
  line
  line `shall for every such offence be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that, when any penalty has been paid in respect of any instrument under section 35, section 40 or section 61, the amount of such penalty shall be allowed in reduction of the fine, (if any) subsequently imposed under this section in respect of the same instrument upon the person who paid such penalty.`
  line
  line `(2) If a share-warrant is issued without being duly stamped, the company issuing the same, and also every person who, at the time when it is issued, is the managing director or secretary or other principal officer of the company, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Arunachal Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Amendment of sections 62.--In the Indian Stamp act, 1899 (2 of 1899) in its application to the state`
  line `of Arunachal Pradesh.`
  line
  line `(1) (i) in section 62, in clause (c), for the words "five hundred rupees", the words "two thousand`
  line `rupees" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `(ii) in section 62, in sub-section (2), for the words "five hundred rupees", the words "five`
  line `thousand rupees" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Arunachal Pradesh Act 3 of 2010, s. 2]`
  line
  line Uttarakhand.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 62.--In sub-section (1) of section 62 of the Principal Act for the words,`
  line `"shall for every such offence, be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees", shall be`
  line `substituted as follows, namely:--`
  line
  line `"shall for every such offence, be punishable with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees".`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttarakhand Act 1 of 2016, s. 10]`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins by Act 5 of 1927, s. 5.`
  line
  line `2. The word "cheque" omitted by s. 5, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (45549)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 77
  title `Penalty for failure to cancel adhesive stamp.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45549&sectionno=63&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `Any person required by section 12 to cancel an`
  line `adhesive stamp, and failing to cancel such stamp in manner prescribed by that section, shall, be punishable with fine which may extend to one hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Arunachal Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Amendment of sections 63,--`
  line
  line `(2) in section 63, for the words "one hundred rupees", the words "five hundred rupees" shall be`
  line substituted.
  line
  line `[Vide Arunachal Pradesh Act 3 of 2010, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (45550)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 78
  title `Penalty for omission to comply with provisions of section 27.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45550&sectionno=64&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `Any person who, with intent to defraud the Government,--`
  line
  line `(a) executes any instrument in which all the facts and circumstances required by section 27 to be`
  line `set forth in such instrument are not fully and truly set forth; or`
  line
  line `(b) being employed or concerned in or about the preparation of any instrument, neglects or omits`
  line `fully and truly to set forth therein all such facts and circumstances; or`
  line
  line `(c) does any other act calculated to deprive the Government of any duty or penalty under this Act;`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 64.--In Section 64 of the Principal Act, the words "and where the`
  line `person is liable to pay the duty shall also be liable to pay the deficient amount of duty" shall be`
  line `added at the end.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 7 of 1987, s. 8]`
  line
  line `Arunachal Pradesh.`
  line
  line `Amendment of sections 64,--`
  line
  line `(3) in section 64, in clause (c), for the words "five thousand rupees", the words "ten thousand rupees"`
  line `shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Arunachal Pradesh Act 3 of 2010, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (45551)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 79
  title `Penalty for refusal to give receipt, and for devices to evade duty on receipts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45551&sectionno=65&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `Any person`
  line who,--
  line
  line `(a) being required under section 30 to give a receipt, refuses or neglects to give the same; or,`
  line
  line `(b) with intent to defraud the Government of any duty, upon a payment of money or delivery of`
  line `property exceeding twenty rupees in amount or value, gives a receipt for an amount or value not`
  line `exceeding twenty rupees, or separates or divides the money or property paid or delivered;`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Arunachal Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Amendment of sections 65,--`
  line
  line `(4) in section 65, in clause (b), for the words "one hundred rupees", the words "five hundred`
  line `rupees" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Arunachal Pradesh 3 of 2010, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (45552)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 80
  title `Penalty for not making out policy or making one not duly stamped.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45552&sectionno=66&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `Any person who--`
  line
  line `(a) receives, or takes credit for, any premium or consideration for any contract of insurance and`
  line `does not, within one month after receiving, or taking credit for, such premium or consideration, make`
  line `out and execute a duly stamped policy of such insurance; or`
  line
  line `(b) makes, executes or delivers out any policy which is not duly stamped, or pays or allows in`
  line `account, or agrees to pay or allow in account, any money upon, or in respect of, any such policy;`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to two hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Arunachal Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Amendment of sections 66,--`
  line
  line `In section 66, in clause (b), for the words"two hundred rupees", the words "five hundred rupees"`
  line `shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Arunachal Pradesh 3 of 2010, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (45553)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 81
  title `Penalty for not drawing full number of bills or marine policies purporting to be in sets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act, 5 of 1927, s. 5.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45553&sectionno=67&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `Any person drawing or executing a bill of exchange ^1[payable otherwise than on demand] or a policy of`
  line `marine insurance purporting to be drawn or executed in a set of two or more, and not at the same time`
  line `drawing or executing on paper duly stamped the whole number of bills or policies of which such bill or`
  line `policy purports the set to consist, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Arunachal Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Amendment of sections 67,--`
  line
  line `In section 67, for the words dbqrsone thousand rupees" the words "two thousand rupees" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Arunachal Pradesh 3 of 2010, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (45554)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 82
  title `Penalty for post-dating bills, and for other devices to defraud the revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45554&sectionno=68&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `Any person`
  line who,--
  line
  line `(a) with intent to defraud the Government of duty, draws, makes or issues any bill of exchange or`
  line `promissory note bearing a date subsequent to that on which such bill or note is actually drawn or`
  line `made; or,`
  line
  line `(b) knowing that such bill or note has been so post-dated, endorses, transfers, presents for`
  line `acceptance or payment, or accepts, pays or receives payment of, such bill or note, or in any manner`
  line `negotiate the same; or,`
  line
  line `(c) with the like intent, practices or is concerned in any act, contrivance or device not specially`
  line `provided for by this Act or any other law for the time being in force;`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Arunachal Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Amendment of sections 68,--`
  line
  line `(7) in section 68, in clause (c), for the words "one thousand rupees", the words "two thousand`
  line `rupees" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Arunachal Pradesh Act 3 of 2010, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (45555)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 83
  title `Penalty for breach of rule relating to sale of stamps and for unauthorised sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1958, s. 10, for "one anna or half an anna" (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45555&sectionno=69&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(a) Any`
  line `person appointed to sell stamps who disobeys any rule made under section 74; and`
  line
  line `(b) any person not so appointed who sells or offers for sale any stamp (other than a ^1ten naye paise`
  line `or five naye paise] adhesive stamp);`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to five hundred rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Arunachal Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `Amendment of sections 69,--`
  line
  line `(8) in section 69, in clause (b), for the words "five hundred rupees", the words "five thousand`
  line `rupees" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Arunachal Pradesh Act 3 of 2010, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (45556)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 84
  title `Institution and conduct of prosecutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45556&sectionno=70&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) No prosecution in respect of any offence`
  line `punishable under this Act or any Act hereby repealed, shall be instituted without the sanction of the`
  line `Collector or such other officer as ^1[the ^2[State Government]] generally, or the Collector specially,`
  line `authorizes in that behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Controlling Revenue-authority, or any officer generally or specially authorized by it in`
  line `this behalf, may stay any such prosecution or compound any such offence.`
  line
  line `(3) The amount of any such composition shall be recoverable in the manner provided by section 48.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "the L.G.".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "collecting Government".`
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (45557)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 85
  title `Jurisdiction of Magistrates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45557&sectionno=71&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `No Magistrate other than a Presidency Magistrate or a Magistrate`
  line `whose powers are not less than those of a Magistrate of the second class, shall try any offence under this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (45558)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 86
  title `Place of trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45558&sectionno=72&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `Every such offence committed in respect of any instrument may be tried in any`
  line `district or presidency-town in which such instrument is found, as well as in any district or presidencytown in which such offence might be tried under the Code of Criminal Procedure for the time being in`
  line force.
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (45559)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 87
  title `Books, etc., to be open to inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45559&sectionno=73&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `Every public officer having in his custody any registers,`
  line `books, records, papers, documents or proceedings, the inspection whereof may tend to secure any duty, or`
  line `to prove or lead to the discovery of any fraud or omission in relation to any duty, shall at all reasonable`
  line `times permit any person authorized in writing by the Collector to inspect for such purpose the registers,`
  line `books, papers, documents and proceedings, and to take such notes and extracts as he may deem`
  line `necessary, without fee or charge.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Amendment of section 73.--For section 73 of the principal Act, the following section shall be`
  line `substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `(1) Every public officer or any person having in his custody any registers, books, records, papers,`
  line `documents or proceedings, the inspections whereof may tend to secure any duty, or to prove or lead to`
  line `the discovery of any fraud or omission in relation to any duty, shall at all reasonable times permit any`
  line `officer authorized in writing by the Collector to enter upon any premises and to inspect for such purposes`
  line `the registers, books, records, papers, documents and proceedings and to take such notes and extracts, as`
  line `he may deem necessary, without fee or charge and if necessary to seize them and impound the same under`
  line `proper acknowledgement:`
  line
  line `Provided that such seizure of any registers, books, records, papers, documents or proceedings in the`
  line `custody of any Bank be made only after a notice of thirty days to make good the deficit of stamp duty is`
  line given.
  line
  line `Explanation--For the purposes of this proviso "Bank" means a banking company as defined in`
  line `section 5 of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 and includes the State Bank of India, constituted by the`
  line `State Bank of India Act, 1955, a subsidiary bank as defined in the State Bank of India (Subsidiary Bank)`
  line `Act, 1959 corresponding new Bank as define in the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of`
  line `Undertakings) Act, 1980, a Regional Rural Bank established under the Regional Rural Bank Act, 1976,`
  line `the Industrial Development Bank of India Act, 1964, National Bank of Agriculture and Rural`
  line `Development Act, 1981, the Life Insurance Corporation Act, 1956, the Industrial Fianc� Corporation of`
  line `India established under the Industrial Finance Corporation Act, 1948, and as such other financial or`
  line `banking institution onwned, controlled or managed by a State Government or the Central Government, as`
  line `may be notified in this behalf by the Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person having in his custody or maintaining such registers, books, records, papers,`
  line `documents or proceedings shall, when so required by the officer authorized under sub-section (1),`
  line `produce them before such officer and at all reasonable times permit such officer to inspect them and take`
  line `such notes and extracts as he may deem necessary.`
  line
  line `(3) if, upon such inspection, the officer so authorized, is of opinion that any instrument is chargeable`
  line `with duty and is not duly stamped, he shall require the payment of the proper duty or the amount required`
  line `to make up the same form the person liable to pay the stamp duty and in case of default the amount of the`
  line `duty shall be recovered as an arrear of land revenue.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 1 of 2003, s. 6]`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 73. --In Explanation to sub-section (1) of Section 73 of the Indian Stamp Act,`
  line `1899, (2 of 1899) for the words and figures "the Industrial Fiance Corporation of India established under`
  line `the Industrial Finance Corporation Act, 1948", the words and figures "other public financial institutions`
  line `notified under Section 4-A of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956)" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 5 of 2004, s. 2]`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Inserted of new section 73-A.—After section 73 of the principal Act, the following section shall be inferred,`
  line `namely :—`
  line
  line `“73-A. Collector’s power to authorize officer to enter premises and inspect certain`
  line `documents.—(1) Where the Collector has reason to believe that all or any of the instruments specified`
  line `in Articles 5 and 43 of the Schedule 1-B have not been charged at all or have been incorrectly charged`
  line `with duty leviable under this Act, he may authorize in writing any officer to enter upon any premises`
  line `where the Collector has reason to believe that any registers, books, records, papers, documents or`
  line `proceedings relating to or in connection with any such instrument are kept and to inspect them, and to`
  line `take such notes and extracts as such officer deems necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person having in his custody or maintaining such registers, books, records, papers,`
  line `documents or proceedings shall at all reasonable times, permit such officer to inspect them and to take`
  line `such notes and extracts as he may deem necessary.`
  line
  line `Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 6 of 1980, s. 10`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 73--In seetion:73-A of the principal Act –`
  line
  line `(a) for sub-section (1) the following sub-section shall be substituted namely :—`
  line
  line `(1) 'Where the Collector has reason to believe that any instrument chargeable to duty has not`
  line `been charged at all or has been incorrectly charged with duty leviable under this Act, he or any`
  line `other Officer authorized by him writing in This behalf may enter upon any premises where the`
  line `Collector has reason to believe that any registers, books, records papers, maps, documents or`
  line `proceedings relating to or in connection with any such instrument are kept and to inspect them`
  line `and to take such notes, copies and extracts as the Collector or such officer deems necessary.`
  line
  line `(b) in sub section (2) after the word ''papers the Word maps and after the word notes the`
  line `word copies” shall be inserted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 22 of 1998, s. 8]`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73_a:
  sectionId (49727)
  sectionNo 73A
  orderNo 88
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=49727&sectionno=73A&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_73_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[73A. Power of Central Government to make rules.--(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the provisions of Part AA of Chapter II.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the Central Government`
  line `may make rules for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of collection of stamp-duty on behalf of the State Government by the stock`
  line `exchange or the clearing corporation authorised by it, from its buyer under clause (a) of sub-section`
  line `(1) of section 9A;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of collection of stamp-duty on behalf of the State Government by the depository`
  line `from the transferor under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 9A;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of collection of stamp-duty on behalf of the State Government by the depository`
  line `from the issuer under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 9A;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of transfer of stamp-duty to the State Government under sub-section (4) of section`
  line 9A;
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which has to be, or may be, provided by rules.]`
obj_root_law_sections_73_b:
  sectionId (50347)
  sectionNo 73B
  orderNo 89
  title `Power to issue directions and to authorise certain authorities to issue instructions, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 12 of 2020, s. 144 (w.e.f. 1-4-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=50347&sectionno=73B&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_73_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[73B. Power to issue directions and to authorise certain authorities to issue instructions, etc.--`
  line `The Central Government may,--`
  line
  line `(a) issue directions relating to such matters and subject to such conditions, as it deems necessary;`
  line
  line `(b) in writing, authorise the Securities and Exchange Board of India established under section 3 of`
  line `the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992) or the Reserve Bank of India`
  line `constituted under section 3 of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934) to issue instructions,`
  line `circulars or guidelines,`
  line
  line `for carrying out the provisions of Part AA of Chapter II and the rules made there under.]`
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (45560)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 90
  title `Powers to make rules relating to sale of stamps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45560&sectionno=74&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `The ^1[State Government] ^2*** may make`
  line `rules for regulating`
  line
  line `(a) the supply and sale of stamps an stamped papers,`
  line
  line `(b) the persons by whom alone such sale is to be conducted, and`
  line
  line `(c) the duties and remuneration of such persons:`
  line
  line `Provided that such rules shall not restrict the sale of ^3[ten naye paise or five naya paise] adhesive`
  line stamps.
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "collecting Government."`
  line
  line `2. The words Subject to the "Control of the G.G. in C" omitted by the A.O.1937.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 19 of 1958 s. 10, for "one anna or half an anna" (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (45561)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 91
  title `Powers to make rules generally to carry out Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "collecting Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45561&sectionno=75&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `The ^1[State Government] may make rules to`
  line `carry out generally the purposes of this Act, and may by such rules prescribe the fines, which shall in no`
  line `case exceed five hundred rupees, to be incurred on breach thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (45562)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 92
  title `Publication of rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45562&sectionno=76&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) All rules made under this Act shall be published in the Official`
  line Gazette.]
  line
  line `(2) All rules published as required by this section shall, upon such publication, have effect as if`
  line `enacted by this Act.`
  line
  line `^2[(2A) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of`
  line `the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.]`
  line
  line `^3[(3) Every rule made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before the State Legislature..]`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2019, s. 20 (w.e.f. 9-1-2020).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 4 of 2005, s. 2 and the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_a:
  sectionId (45563)
  sectionNo 76A
  orderNo 93
  title `Delegation of certain powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45563&sectionno=76A&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_76_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[76A. Delegation of certain powers .--^2[^3*** The State Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette], delegate`
  line
  line `(a) all or any of the powers conferred on it by sections 2(9), 33(3), ( b ), 70(1), 74 and 78 to the`
  line `Chief Controlling Revenue-authority; and`
  line
  line `(b) all or any of the powers conferred on the Chief Controlling Revenue-authority by sections 45 (1), (2), 56 (1) and 70 (2) to such subordinate Revenue-authority as may be specified in the`
  line `notification. ]`
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Uttar Pradesh`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 76-A to Act no. II of 1899.--In section 76-A of the Indian Stamp Act, 1899, as`
  line `amended in its application to Uttar Pradesh, in clause (b) for the figures 56 (1) the figures and letter 56`
  line `(1) (1-A) shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Uttar Pradesh Act 1 of 2016, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_76_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1914, s. 2 and the Sch. Pt. I.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for The Local Government may, by notification in the Local Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `3. The words, figures and brackets The Central Government subject to the provision of section 124(1) of the`
  line `Government of India Act, 1935, and omitted by the A.O. 1950.`
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (45564)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 94
  title `Saving as to court-fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45564&sectionno=77&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act contained shall be deemed to affect the duties`
  line `chargeable under any enactment for the time being in force relating to court-fee.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line `Himachal Pradesh.--`
  line
  line `At the beginning of section 77 of the said Act the following words shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"Except for the provisions as to copies contained in section 6-A".`
  line
  line `[Vide Himachal Pradesh Act 4 of 1953, s. 11]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Section 77-A, Act 2 of 1899.–--After section 77 of the principal Act the following new section shall`
  line `be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `77-A. Fractions of five naye paise to be rounded off.-- In the determination of the amount of duly`
  line `payable or of allowance to be made under this Act, any fraction of five naye paise shall be rounded off to`
  line `the next higher five naye paise.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 35 of 1962, s. 3]`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77_a:
  sectionId (45565)
  sectionNo 77A
  orderNo 95
  title `Saving as to certain stamps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 19 of 1958, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45565&sectionno=77A&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_77_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[77A. Saving as to certain stamps. ---All stamps in denominations of annas four or multiples`
  line `thereof shall be deemed to be stamps of the value of twenty-five naye paise or, as the case may be,`
  line `multiples thereof and shall, accordingly, be valid for all the purposes of this Act.]`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Orissa.--
  line
  line `Repeal of section 77-A, (Act 2 of 1899).--- Section 77-A of the Indian Stamp Act, 1899 (2 of 1899)`
  line `(hereinafter referred a to as the principal Act), shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Orissa Act 9 of 1970, s. 2]`
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (45566)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 96
  title `Act to be translated, and sold cheaply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., "four annas" (w.e.f. 1-10-1958).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45566&sectionno=78&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `Every State Government shall make provision for the`
  line `sale of translations of this Act in the principal vernacular languages of the territories administered by it at`
  line `a price not exceeding ^1[twenty-five naye paise] per copy.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line ASSAM--
  line
  line `Substitution of section 78.--In the principal Act, for section 78, the following shall be substituted,`
  line namely,--
  line
  line `"78. Duty or allowance to be rounded off to 78 the next rupee.--If the total amount of`
  line `duty payable, or of allowance to be made under this Act is not a round figure, the total amount`
  line `shall be rounded off the next rupee."`
  line
  line `[Vide Assam Act 22 of 2004, s. 5]`
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (45567)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 97
  title [Repealed.].
  content `[ Repealed.] Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 1914 (10 of 1914) s. 3 and schedule II.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436&sectionId=45567&sectionno=79&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00036_189902_1523339055436
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
